System requirements
===================

   Versions 2.5 and below may be played on any Amiga with 1 megabyte of
ram and OS 1.2 or higher. Yes, even if you have an old 1985 A1000 with
Kickstart 1.2 you can play this great game so long as you have 1 meg or
more of ram.

   The authors went to great lengths and much trouble to ensure
compatiblity with all the old Amigas. We hope you enjoy the fruits of
our labors.

   Version 2.5 is the LAST version that will work on any Amiga with 1
meg of ram. ALL versions above 2.3d require at least 2 megs of ram, a
hard drive, at least OS 1.2 or higher and a Motorola 68000 CPU or
higher.

   2.5d = demo version. 2.5f = full version which only registered users
can obtain. The demo version cannot load games, and stops at turn 18.

   Chaos 2.6 will work under at least Workbench 1.2, 1.3, 2.04, 3.0 and
3.1 and should work on anything subsequent. It requires an Amiga
supporting PAL mode. All Amigas manufactured since 1989 support PAL
mode. Any Amiga manufactured before 1989 supports PAL mode if it has
been upgraded with an enhanced Agnes chip. (Enhanced Denise chip not
needed).

   Version 2.71 is the LAST version that will work with an OS less than
3.0

   Version 2.81 and up all require a 68020 processor or higher and OS
3.0 or higher.

   If you live in the USA or Canada then you'll need to boot your
computer into PAL mode. The best way to do this is to use the program
"degrader", though in this case you aren't going to actually degrade
anything. With degrader select "50 Hz", "50 Hz System" and "Survive
Resets" and your Amiga will be rebooted in PAL mode and will think it
is in a European country operating in PAL mode.

   Normally a North American Amiga operates in NTSC mode 640x400
resolution.  PAL mode produces a resolution of 640x512.

   Chaos makes use of the @{b}narrator.device@{ub} and @{b}req.library@{ub}. As of
version 2.2 Chaos no longer makes any use of @{b}ReqTools.library@{ub}.

   If the @{b}-t@{ub} option is used the @{b}translator.library@{ub} is also used.  Other
required files are the executable @{b}chaos@{ub} and the data files @{b}pool.ssc@{ub} and
@{b}chaos.prb@{ub} all of which must reside in the current directory when Chaos
is started. There are various other fonts, music and Sounds files which
reside in the directories of the same name within the current directory.

   The @{b}-t@{ub} option forces translation of player names for the speech and
requires the @{b}translator.library@{ub}. A few other options are supported, to
find out about these use @{b}chaos -h@{ub} and then press @{b}left Amiga-M@{ub} to return
to the CLI screen.


