Adding your own sound effects
-----------------------------

   Beginning with Chaos v2.81 it is very easy to add your own sound
effects into the game.

   Once you have a sound effect that you want in the game you must save
it as a @{b}.8svx@{ub} sound file.

   In the @{b}Chaos@{ub} game directory there is a @{b}Sounds/@{ub} directory. In that
dir are 3 other directories @{b}Combat/@{ub} @{b}Death/@{ub} and @{b}Kill/@{ub}.

   The @{b}Combat/@{ub} directory contains the sounds that play when a creature
attacks another in hand-to-hand combat.

   The @{b}Death/@{ub} directory contains the sounds that play when a creature
dies.

   The @{b}Kill/@{ub} directory contains the sounds that play when a creature
kills something.

   So let's say you have a really great sound that the Mind Flayer
should make when it attacks someone. Just put the sound effect into the
@{b}Combat/@{ub} directory under the name of @{b}Mind Flayer@{ub}. The filename of the
sound effect must @{i}EXACTLY@{ui} match the name of the creature in the game!
You @{i}MUST@{ui} use correct spacing and uppercase/lowercase letters.

   If you add new sounds in the middle of a game then you must quit the
game completely (exit back to workbench). Then restart the game and the
sounds will then be activated.

   If you have a sound that you would like to play when a Mind Flayer
dies then just put it in the @{b}Death/@{ub} directory with the name @{b}Mind Flayer@{ub}.

   If you have a sound that you would like to play whenever a Mind
Flayer kills something then put it in the @{b}Kill/@{ub} directory with the name
@{b}Mind Flayer@{ub}.

   Using this system you can implement special sounds for any and all
of the monsters in Chaos.


@EndNode

