Abath
=====

   A variation on the unicorn having a somewhat enlarged horn which it
can use to induce severe bruising in an opponent.  The abath can also
be ridden by the wizard.

   For many years the existence of the creature was the subject of much
debate, and only recently have any instances come to life.


@EndNode

@Node "Abduction" "Chaos.Guide/Abduction"
@Next "Achiyalabopa"
@Prev "Abath"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Abduction
=========

   Like subversion, abduction is an attempt to convince an enemy
creature that its interests may better lie with allegiance to your
wizard.  Intelligent creatures are more likely to see through this ruse
than stupid creatures.  However, as abduction applies to a random
creature you cannot know beforehand the intelligence of the recipient.
Further, because the targeting of this spell is so imprecise it is
possible that it will be applied to one of your own creations.
Therefore, the spell is most beneficial when you have relatively few
creations.

   Line of sight is not required and your chosen target can be anywhere
on the board.  This spell will not attempt to target Artifacts,
Scrolls, Wizards or corpses.  If successful, the target will
immediately come under control of your wizard and no longer respond to
the commands of its previous lord.


@EndNode

@Node "Achiyalabopa" "Chaos.Guide/Achiyalabopa"
@Next "AcidRain"
@Prev "Abduction"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Achiyalabopa
============

   A large low-flying bird with poor eyesight.  The history of this
creature is unclear, but it has evolved feathers which resemble knives.
It attacks simply by brushing against the opponent.  The knife-like
feathers are sharp enough to make a large number of serrations on the
hides of the opponent.


@EndNode

@Node "AcidRain" "Chaos.Guide/AcidRain"
@Next "AerialServant"
@Prev "Achiyalabopa"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Acid Rain
=========

   Causes a global rain storm with droplets of extreme acidity.  The
rain drops are a mixture of water, sulphuric acid, formic acid, nitric
acid, phosphoric acid, carbonic acid, and surprisingly citric acid.
The droplets also contain hydrazine and various other flammable
compounds.  Because of these flammable compounds acid rain will not put
out fires.  Further, acid rain does not harm creatures in general
although during the rain it may be painful to them.

   However, trees are extremely vulnerable to this type of rain.  Even
the hardy magic wood cannot stand acid rain.


@EndNode

@Node "AerialServant" "Chaos.Guide/AerialServant"
@Next "Aesculapius"
@Prev "AcidRain"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Aerial Servant
==============

   An aerial servant is a semi-intelligent air spirit and can only be
dimly seen.  They have no effect in combat, but their high vitality
makes them an ideal blocking creature.  They can move almost anywhere
in a single bound and have reasonable agility.


@EndNode

@Node "Aesculapius" "Chaos.Guide/Aesculapius"
@Next "Agathion"
@Prev "AerialServant"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Aesculapius
===========

   The ancient Roman god of healing and medicine.  Known to the ancient
Greeks as Asklepios.


@EndNode

@Node "Agathion" "Chaos.Guide/Agathion"
@Next "AirElemental"
@Prev "Aesculapius"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Agathion
========

   A powerful and helpful race which have descended from the stars.
Although appearing in humanoid form, this is not their natural form.
Their true form is unknown.  The agathion are not physically strong but
can cast a limited number of spells which they perform on their own
accord.  They are known to be able to cast bless, cure, haste, magic
shield, and vitality.


@EndNode

@Node "AirElemental" "Chaos.Guide/AirElemental"
@Next "Alliance"
@Prev "Agathion"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Air Elemental
=============

   A powerful elemental best kept well clear of by mortal creatures.
Upon its death the air elemental becomes a tempest.


@EndNode

@Node "Alliance" "Chaos.Guide/Alliance"
@Next "AlterReality"
@Prev "AirElemental"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Alliance
========

   Force another wizard to enter into an alliance with you.  The target
wizard joins your team and that wizard's creations will no longer
engage your creatures.  You can even force several wizards into
alliances with you by using multiple alliance spells.  When allied with
a computer player, the computer wizard will not cast harmful spells on
your wizard.

   The independents are FIERCELY independent and don't want to be in an
alliance with you (or anyone else for that matter).  So don't bother
trying it on them.


@EndNode

@Node "AlterReality" "Chaos.Guide/AlterReality"
@Next "Alternography"
@Prev "Alliance"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Alter Reality
=============

   This spell can be cast on any creature provided it is not dead.  The
spell will cause the creature to undergo a metamorphosis to a new
creature type.  This spell can turn orcs into dragons and vampires into
ogres.

   The result is random.


@EndNode

@Node "Alternography" "Chaos.Guide/Alternography"
@Next "Amphisbaena"
@Prev "AlterReality"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Alternography
=============

   Alternography allows you to see the world through the eyes of an
alternate wizard.  Any wizard possessing the power of Alternography can
instantly view the entire plane of existence through the eyes of any
other wizard simply by pressing ALT # So if you want to see which parts
of the world that player 2 has mapped just press ALT 2.


@EndNode

@Node "Amphisbaena" "Chaos.Guide/Amphisbaena"
@Next "Anger"
@Prev "Alternography"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Amphisbaena
===========

   A fairly powerful two headed snake that kills its prey by
constriction.  This creature is easy to kill.


@EndNode

@Node "Anger" "Chaos.Guide/Anger"
@Next "Animate"
@Prev "Amphisbaena"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Anger
=====

   Anger is a powerful spell which will make all your creatures very
angry at their opponents. As a result their combat ability will be
raised by 1 point.


@EndNode

@Node "Animate" "Chaos.Guide/Animate"
@Next "AppleWood"
@Prev "Anger"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Animate
=======

   This spell causes several different inanimate objects to become
living creatures.  The spell can be cast on any player, but it is
usually the best option to cast the spell on yourself.

   This spell has no effect on generators.


@EndNode

@Node "AppleWood" "Chaos.Guide/AppleWood"
@Next "Arborist"
@Prev "Animate"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Apple Wood
==========

   This spell allows a wizard to produce two apple trees.  While useful
blocking objects the trees have another use.  Any creature on your team
adjacent to an apple tree will have its magical resistance boosted by
one unit per round.

   The trees cannot be used for meditation or in combat.


@EndNode

@Node "Arborist" "Chaos.Guide/Arborist"
@Next "Archerotomy"
@Prev "AppleWood"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Arborist
========

   Special training for the wizard in the cultivation of trees.  A
wizard having this training is able to cast trees next to each other.


@EndNode

@Node "Archerotomy" "Chaos.Guide/Archerotomy"
@Next "Archery"
@Prev "Arborist"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Archerotomy
===========

   The victim of this spell will have its archery abilty surgically
removed.

   This spell works over the entire world and does not require line of
sight.  2 attempts are granted.


@EndNode

@Node "Archery" "Chaos.Guide/Archery"
@Next "ArcticWolf"
@Prev "Archerotomy"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Archery
=======

   The target is given the archery powerup.  This spell is only
meaningful for objects having ranged combat.  It will have little
effect on other creatures.  Further, there is little point in casting
this spell on creatures (like elves) which already have this ability.
Ideal targets are dragons, bolters, and wizards with bows.

   After receiving this spell line of sight will not be required for
ranged combat.


@EndNode

@Node "ArcticWolf" "Chaos.Guide/ArcticWolf"
@Next "Armour"
@Prev "Archery"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Arctic Wolf
===========

   A wolf from the extreme cold regions.  A horrid carnivore that will
eat whenever possible.  Because they normally inhabit a harsh
environment they are very hardy.  They do not fear the undead.  They do
not fear dragons either.  They attack multiple characteristics and
enjoy ripping off the legs of their prey.  They can hear 2x as far as
they can see and they can smell 4x as far as they can see.  Wolves are
scavengers.


@EndNode

@Node "Armour" "Chaos.Guide/Armour"
@Next "Aviary"
@Prev "ArcticWolf"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Armour
======

   Armour can be used to boost the defences of any creature.  A good
candidate to armour is your wizard.  Armour adds a third of the maximum
life to the selected creature.  You can apply armour to enemy creatures
if desired.

   Line of sight is not required and the spell works over the entire
world.


@EndNode

@Node "Aviary" "Chaos.Guide/Aviary"
@Next "Azer"
@Prev "Armour"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Aviary
======

   This is like the general purpose generator but is somewhat weaker
and only produces a limited number of races.  It is capable of
generating most of the bird species.

   Casting such a generator will ensure that you always have a fresh
supply of flying creatures even if not a strong army.


@EndNode

@Node "Azer" "Chaos.Guide/Azer"
@Next "Baboon"
@Prev "Aviary"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Azer
====

   A creature which in appearence resembles an orc.  They are masters
of fire and are hot to the touch.  They show a lack of compassion for
most things, and although they can control fires at will they very
rarely feel any motivation to do so.


@EndNode

@Node "Baboon" "Chaos.Guide/Baboon"
@Next "BallLightning"
@Prev "Azer"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Baboon
======

   The baboon is not particularly useful.  All its qualities are
somewhat less than those of the gorilla, except for its superior
agility.


@EndNode

@Node "BallLightning" "Chaos.Guide/BallLightning"
@Next "Banderlog"
@Prev "Baboon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ball Lightning
==============

   An energized ball of lightning which severely damages the target's
combat ability.  Inflicts 6 points of damage to the target's combat
ability with any excess damage being transferred to the target's life
force at a 2:1 ratio.  Thus using this spell on a creature with 1
combat point would result in its combat being reduced to 0 and its life
force being reduced by 10 points.


@EndNode

@Node "Banderlog" "Chaos.Guide/Banderlog"
@Next "Bandit"
@Prev "BallLightning"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Banderlog
=========

   A variant of the baboon which is somewhat weaker than a gorilla.
They can help keep the numbers up in a battle but are little use as a
single agent.


@EndNode

@Node "Bandit" "Chaos.Guide/Bandit"
@Next "BasaltGolem"
@Prev "Banderlog"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Bandit
======

   A human mercenary that generally behaves as a thief and general
rogue.  Often they enjoy the taste of battle and will fight for
nothing.  They quickly become bored from lack of action and are not
particularly reliable or trustworthy.

   This said, they enjoy mingling with other creatures of all types,
forever on the lookout for quick financial gain.  Maybe they are
related to lawyers.


@EndNode

@Node "BasaltGolem" "Chaos.Guide/BasaltGolem"
@Next "Basilisk"
@Prev "Bandit"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Basalt Golem
============

   A form of golem made from basalt.  They are marginally more
intelligent than the usual stone golem.  One advantage is an ability to
move considerably faster than other golems, since basalt holds together
better when moving at speed.  However, the main advantage is an ability
to gaze at other creatures and almost paralyze them.


@EndNode

@Node "Basilisk" "Chaos.Guide/Basilisk"
@Next "Bat"
@Prev "BasaltGolem"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Basilisk
========

   The basilisk is a reptilian monster whose slow metabolic process
allows it only slow movement.  It has powerful jaws and a penetrating
gaze which many foes find unsettling.  They are stubborn and strong.


@EndNode

@Node "Bat" "Chaos.Guide/Bat"
@Next "BattleCry"
@Prev "Basilisk"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Bat
===

   Although the bat is weak, flight allows it to be a persistent menace
to slower moving ground-ridden species.


@EndNode

@Node "BattleCry" "Chaos.Guide/BattleCry"
@Next "Betrayal"
@Prev "Bat"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Battle Cry
==========

   Causes your wizard to produce a sonic shock wave consisting of an
order to battle hard.  The sound is guaranteed to stir your creatures
into action.  All your combatants will attack at double strength.  The
voice is so strong that creatures will exceed the normal maximum for
combat if necessary.

   The effect lasts only for the duration of the current round.  The
spell is most useful when you have many weaker creatures and want one
quick chance to wipe out many of the opposition.


@EndNode

@Node "Betrayal" "Chaos.Guide/Betrayal"
@Next "Biohazard"
@Prev "BattleCry"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Betrayal
========

   Betrayal is an attempt to convince an enemy creature that its
interests might be better served by changing its allegiance.  It is
essentially a weak version of subversion, as the convincing is only one
way.  That is, although the creature may be convinced to change sides
there is little chance that it will decide upon your lord as its new
leader.

   However, the spell is still useful because it works over a longer
distance than subversion and no wizard likes any adjacent creature to
suddenly become an enemy.


@EndNode

@Node "Biohazard" "Chaos.Guide/Biohazard"
@Next "BipedalGenerator"
@Prev "Betrayal"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Biohazard
=========

   Releases a deadly but selective toxin into the air which will cause
infections to run amuck in the wounds of the enemy.

   All enemy creatures will be slower at recovering from any wounds they
receive.


@EndNode

@Node "BipedalGenerator" "Chaos.Guide/BipedalGenerator"
@Next "BirdLord"
@Prev "Biohazard"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Bipedal Generator
=================

   This is a like the general purpose generator but is somewhat weaker
and only produces a limited number of races.  It is capable of
generating most of the weaker bipedal races.

   Casting such a generator will ensure that you always have a fresh
supply of blocking creatures even if not a strong army.


@EndNode

@Node "BirdLord" "Chaos.Guide/BirdLord"
@Next "Bless"
@Prev "BipedalGenerator"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Bird Lord
=========

   A bird lord is a king of the avian species.  Often bird lords are
mistaken as eagles.  Bird lords can heal any wounds they receive at a
phenomenal rate.  They are amongst the fastest of all creatures and are
well learned.  Most magic will have little effect on them.  The bird
lord possesses adequate combat skill and can easily flee from danger.
The biggest boon of the bird lord is its ability to fire an extremely
acidic salvo an immense distance.


@EndNode

@Node "Bless" "Chaos.Guide/Bless"
@Next "BloodWorm"
@Prev "BirdLord"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Bless
=====

   The bless spell is used to improve the overall morale and strength
of a wizard and creations.  Every creation of the casting wizard's,
including inanimate objects and growths receives a small boost in life.

   Bless spells are best cast when you have many creations or when your
wizard is starting to founder.  You cannot bless the creations of
another player.


@EndNode

@Node "BloodWorm" "Chaos.Guide/BloodWorm"
@Next "BlueDragon"
@Prev "Bless"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Blood Worm
==========

   The Blood Worm inflicts less damage than a regular worm but this is
compensated by the fact that the Blood Worm injects poison with each
attack. It has a lower recovery rate than the standard Worm so it needs
to constantly feed in order to replenish its life force.

   In all other respects the Blood Worm is identical to the standard
Worm.


@EndNode

@Node "BlueDragon" "Chaos.Guide/BlueDragon"
@Next "Bodak"
@Prev "BloodWorm"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Blue Dragon
===========

   The blue dragon is very dangerous and can emit an electrical
discharge across ten cells given line of sight.  Blue dragons normally
have little to do with other species and a summons can only be obtained
by meditation.

   A blue dragon is stronger than a red dragon.


@EndNode

@Node "Bodak" "Chaos.Guide/Bodak"
@Next "Boil"
@Prev "BlueDragon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Bodak
=====

   A Bodak is a human that has become corrupted by venturing too close
to the abyssal planes.  They appear in giant proportions and fight bare
handed even though most of them do carry a weapon.

   Their combat ability is similar to that of a true giant, but they
retain only the stamina of a real human.


@EndNode

@Node "Boil" "Chaos.Guide/Boil"
@Next "Bolter"
@Prev "Bodak"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Boil
====

   Causes a very specific cadence of microwaves to cover the world.
They are at a precise value which causes large bodies of water to
evaporate.

   Any floods and pools will be destroyed.


@EndNode

@Node "Bolter" "Chaos.Guide/Bolter"
@Next "BrainBoost"
@Prev "Boil"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Bolter
======

   A piece of wall augmented with a very high energy psionic arrow
launcher.  The bolter can fire one arrow per turn with deadly force
over a medium distance.  Line of sight is required.


@EndNode

@Node "BrainBoost" "Chaos.Guide/BrainBoost"
@Next "BrainDrain"
@Prev "Bolter"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Brain Boost
===========

   This spell can be cast on any creature and exponentially increases
the number of synaptic connections in the mental faculties of the chosen
target.  The spell is best used to protect a wizard against the brain
drain spell.

   This spell increases the target's intelligence to maximum.


@EndNode

@Node "BrainDrain" "Chaos.Guide/BrainDrain"
@Next "BrainDrainBeam"
@Prev "BrainBoost"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Brain Drain
===========

   This spell will play on the mind of the chosen target.  The spell
induces torment in the brain of the target causing severe synaptic
damage.  For weak minded creatures the spell is usually fatal.  Damage
caused by a brain drain spell may be recoverable by a brain boost
spell.  This spell can be cast on enemy wizards.

   This spell inflicts 10 points of damage to the target's
intelligence; if this results in a value less than zero then the target
dies of stupidity.


@EndNode

@Node "BrainDrainBeam" "Chaos.Guide/BrainDrainBeam"
@Next "BrownBear"
@Prev "BrainDrain"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Brain Drain Beam
================

   Causes your wizard to emit a beam of Brain Draining.  All creatures
in the chosen direction will lose 10 points of intelligence.  Any
creature thus reduced to less than 0 intelligence will die.  The Brain
Drain Beam affects your own creatures as well as your enemies, so be
careful where you cast it.

   This spell does not affect inanimate objects, growths or scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "BrownBear" "Chaos.Guide/BrownBear"
@Next "BurstroemsBrowser"
@Prev "BrainDrainBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Brown Bear
==========

   A very strong and skilled animal, the brown bear is a tough match
for a lion.  Like the lion the brown bear is very ferocious in attack.
The brown bear is not particularly agile and once engaged the bear must
usually fight to the death.  A brown bear can be killed by the rarer
but more powerful grizzly bear.


@EndNode

@Node "BurstroemsBrowser" "Chaos.Guide/BurstroemsBrowser"
@Next "Bury"
@Prev "BrownBear"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Burstroem's Browser
===================

   Forged in the magical land of Scandinavia by Burstroem the
BattleMage.  This object empowers the owner with limited Lexmnemancy.
It allows the owning wizard to browse through other wizard's
spell-lists to see what spells they have.

   During the spell-selection phase, just press CTRL-# to browse through
another player's spell-list.  E.  G.  press ctrl-2 to peek at player 2's
spell-list.


@EndNode

@Node "Bury" "Chaos.Guide/Bury"
@Next "Camel"
@Prev "BurstroemsBrowser"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Bury
====

   Allows a wizard to bury up to eight corpses and/or scrolls from
anywhere on the board.  Line of sight is not required.

   Once buried a dead creature cannot be raised from the dead.
Therefore, by burying corpses of dragons, giants, and so on, you can
prevent other wizards from raising them.  The spell is also useful for
clearing space for walls, trees, and meditation chambers or for
destroying scrolls that you don't want your enemies to grab.


@EndNode

@Node "Camel" "Chaos.Guide/Camel"
@Next "Cartography"
@Prev "Bury"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Camel
=====

   The camel can be ridden by the wizard and is useful in this respect.
As well as normal attack the camel can spit at nearby targets and
although the spit is not potent it can sometimes be the difference
between life and death.


@EndNode

@Node "Cartography" "Chaos.Guide/Cartography"
@Next "CatLord"
@Prev "Camel"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Cartography
===========

   This spell gives your team magical training in the cartographical
arts.

   The net effect is that all creatures on your team will be able to
accurately map an additional 1.5 squares distance in all directions.


@EndNode

@Node "CatLord" "Chaos.Guide/CatLord"
@Next "Centaur"
@Prev "Cartography"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Cat Lord
========

   The Cat Lord will assist a wizard when required but is not
particularly suited to combat.

   However, as master of all cats, the Cat Lord has some important
abilities.  When first cast the Cat Lord will immediately take all cats
under his control.  He is also able to summon his own lions, jaguars,
and leopards.


@EndNode

@Node "Centaur" "Chaos.Guide/Centaur"
@Next "Chainsaw"
@Prev "CatLord"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Centaur
=======

   The centaur has the head and torso of a man and the abdomen and legs
of a horse.  A centaur may be ridden by the wizard.  The centaur
carries a bow which often comes in handy.  The centaur is superior to
the horse in most respects.


@EndNode

@Node "Chainsaw" "Chaos.Guide/Chainsaw"
@Next "ChaosLord"
@Prev "Centaur"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Chainsaw
========

   The Chainsaw is a dangerous mêlée weapon of terrible power.  In
ancient times (circa 20th century Earth) a small band of humans armed
with this weapon could wipe out entire forests of trees in a short time.

   This fearsome weapon works equally well on the flesh of living
creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "ChaosLord" "Chaos.Guide/ChaosLord"
@Next "Charm"
@Prev "Chainsaw"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Chaos Lord
==========

   A wizard casting this spell will be completely enlightened to the
entire universe and become essentially immortal.  A wizard possessing
the level of potency induced by this spell will not need support
creatures, mounts, nor undeads.

   Such a wizard may freely go hand to hand with a demon and still
expect to win easily.  All other players will need to forget their
petty squabbles if they are to defeat you.

   If you have this spell on your list it should be used immediately, no
matter what the circumstances.  This spell induces a state more powerful
than the highly sought after Touch of God spell.  Besides giving the
wizard full strength in all vital statistics the wizard will also
receive the triple power up, a bow, wings, fire shield, flood shield,
earthquake shield, reflector, pox shield, and quickshot.


@EndNode

@Node "Charm" "Chaos.Guide/Charm"
@Next "Chronomancer"
@Prev "ChaosLord"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Charm
=====

   All creatures on the board will feel a tug towards your wizard.
Those of lesser intelligence may be so swayed by your words that they
change to your side.


@EndNode

@Node "Chronomancer" "Chaos.Guide/Chronomancer"
@Next "ClayGolem"
@Prev "Charm"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Chronomancer
============

   A Chronomancer is a wizard who specializes in the magic of time.
They are fond of vanishing their enemies into the future.


@EndNode

@Node "ClayGolem" "Chaos.Guide/ClayGolem"
@Next "Cloak"
@Prev "Chronomancer"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Clay Golem
==========

   As the name suggests these unintelligent creations are made of clay
and therefore can take much punishment.

   They are quite susceptible to magic attack and are somewhat weaker
than the stone golem.


@EndNode

@Node "Cloak" "Chaos.Guide/Cloak"
@Next "Coercion"
@Prev "ClayGolem"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Cloak
=====

   The Cloak can be used to place a shroud around any creature on the
board, but it cannot be applied to inanimate objects, growths, corpses
or scrolls.  The Cloak can be cast on creatures not owned by the caster
including sleeping creatures.

   This spell can be cast anywhere in the world and does not require
line of sight.  Once cloaked, information about the cloaked creature
can only be obtained by its owner.  Any cloaked creature becomes 4x as
hard to hit because it is not easily seen by its opponents and this is
the main reason for using the cloak.

   A cloaked creature blocks the LOS of its enemies but you, your
creations and your allies will be able to see straight through it.  A
Cloak may be removed with Reveal.


@EndNode

@Node "Coercion" "Chaos.Guide/Coercion"
@Next "Combat"
@Prev "Cloak"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Coercion
========

   A mental assault against all the other wizards.  The other wizards
will have difficulty staving off the onslaught and they will not have
time to select a spell in the subsequent round.

   While most wizards will shake of the effects of the spell within one
round, some wizards may suffer for several rounds.  This spell is
useful in the early stages of the game and gives you a chance to get
ahead of the other wizards.


@EndNode

@Node "Combat" "Chaos.Guide/Combat"
@Next "CombatDrainBeam"
@Prev "Coercion"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Combat
======

   This spell provides the recipient with advanced weapons and tactical
skills.  The result is a very mean fighting machine capable of killing
very strong opponents in a short time.  Even the humble halfling
becomes a deadly weapon upon receiving this special training.


@EndNode

@Node "CombatDrainBeam" "Chaos.Guide/CombatDrainBeam"
@Next "Command"
@Prev "Combat"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Combat Drain Beam
=================

   Causes your wizard to emit a beam of Combat Draining which will
drain 8 points of combat from EVERYTHING in the chosen direction.  This
beam affects your own creatures as well as your enemies.  It will not
reduce below 0.


@EndNode

@Node "Command" "Chaos.Guide/Command"
@Next "Confidence"
@Prev "CombatDrainBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Command
=======

   Command increases the ability of a wizard to direct its creations.

   In particular, creatures will find it easier to escape from
conflicts if required to do so.


@EndNode

@Node "Confidence" "Chaos.Guide/Confidence"
@Next "Consecrate"
@Prev "Command"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Confidence
==========

   Places a blanket of calmness over your creations.  Your living
creatures will no longer fear the undead and will be able to attack the
undead.

   The effect lasts for three rounds.


@EndNode

@Node "Consecrate" "Chaos.Guide/Consecrate"
@Next "Convert"
@Prev "Confidence"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Consecrate
==========

   A spell similar to Dark Power but affecting a wider area.  Choose the
centre and this spot and all cells immediately adjacent will suffer two
points of damage to their magic resistance.  Useful for destroying
groups of weak undead creatures.

   For some unknown reason, this spell must be cast directly on a
creature of some type; a corpse or empty cell won't do.


@EndNode

@Node "Convert" "Chaos.Guide/Convert"
@Next "ConwellsCowCatapult"
@Prev "Consecrate"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Convert
=======

   The target will be converted from undead to living.  Does not affect
any other stats.  Up to 2 things may be converted.


@EndNode

@Node "ConwellsCowCatapult" "Chaos.Guide/ConwellsCowCatapult"
@Next "CrimsonDeath"
@Prev "Convert"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Conwell's Cow Catapult
======================

   An ancient artifact of fearsome power.  Conwell used this weapon to
hurl cows at Irvine during the last Wizard War.  Irvine suffered such
horrible afflictions from this war machine that he was forced to develop
Irvine's Invulnerability to protect himself from the ensuing bovine
barrage.


@EndNode

@Node "CrimsonDeath" "Chaos.Guide/CrimsonDeath"
@Next "Crocodile"
@Prev "ConwellsCowCatapult"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Crimson Death
=============

   A pale vapourous creature named after its colour.  There is nothing
particularly special about the creature and it is yet another creature
from the spirit world.


@EndNode

@Node "Crocodile" "Chaos.Guide/Crocodile"
@Next "CrystalBall"
@Prev "CrimsonDeath"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Crocodile
=========

   Although the crocodile is stupid, any living creature which
approaches one is a bigger fool.  The crocodile is a good match for a
lion or a bear, having a high endurance.  Usually the crocodile can
sidle away from danger if desired.


@EndNode

@Node "CrystalBall" "Chaos.Guide/CrystalBall"
@Next "Cure"
@Prev "Crocodile"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Crystal Ball
============

   A highly desirable spell which removes the need for your wizard to
have line of sight in order to cast a spell.

   With the Crystal Ball, your wizard can "see" everywhere.  Range
restrictions still apply as usual.


@EndNode

@Node "Cure" "Chaos.Guide/Cure"
@Next "Curse"
@Prev "CrystalBall"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Cure
====

   All creatures have felt the ravages of the pox at some time.  This
spell is useful in ending a major plague.

   All creatures infected with the pox will be cured of the disease.


@EndNode

@Node "Curse" "Chaos.Guide/Curse"
@Next "CursedSword"
@Prev "Cure"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Curse
=====

   The curse is a highly desirable spell.  It is best cast when the
world is full of many enemy creations and your position is reasonably
secure.  Curse will suck 2 points of life from all enemy creatures,
growths, and even inanimate objects.  Sleeping creatures are also
drained.

   Any creature whose life is exhausted by the curse will be killed and
points credited to the casting wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "CursedSword" "Chaos.Guide/CursedSword"
@Next "Dalek"
@Prev "Curse"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Cursed Sword
============

   Works over the entire world and does not require line of sight.  The
recipient of the Cursed Sword will lose 5 points of combat (will not go
below 0) and will suddenly not be able to attack undeads.


@EndNode

@Node "Dalek" "Chaos.Guide/Dalek"
@Next "Dao"
@Prev "CursedSword"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dalek
=====

   This well known time-traveller can be a useful addition to any
campaign.  Their sole purpose in life is the extermination of other
forms of life and they are reasonably adept at carrying out this task.
However, daleks are made of relatively cheap and weak metal.


@EndNode

@Node "Dao" "Chaos.Guide/Dao"
@Next "DarkCitadel"
@Prev "Dalek"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dao
===

   A genie of particularly evil alignment.  This genie will, on its own
accord, curse the enemy in your name.  Dao are also known to make use of
the drain, invert, pox, and slow spells.


@EndNode

@Node "DarkCitadel" "Chaos.Guide/DarkCitadel"
@Next "DarkPower"
@Prev "Dao"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dark Citadel
============

   The dark citadel provides a safe haven for the wizard, and a place
for meditation.  There is a chance of the citadel collapsing at each
turn, if this should happen while the wizard is inside a new spell will
be granted.

   It is possible to make use of dark citadels conjured by other wizards
provided they are not already occupied.  Only a wizard can make use of a
citadel.  A dark citadel can be destroyed by an extremely determined
attacker.


@EndNode

@Node "DarkPower" "Chaos.Guide/DarkPower"
@Next "DarkWood"
@Prev "DarkCitadel"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dark Power
==========

   Dark power causes the target to be consumed by madness.  A high
magical resistance is required to escape the effect.

   3 attempts are granted, each of which inflicts 2 points of damage to
the creature's magical resistance.  Dark power does not require line of
sight and works over the entire world.  Dark power cannot be applied to
inanimate objects.


@EndNode

@Node "DarkWood" "Chaos.Guide/DarkWood"
@Next "DeadRevenge"
@Prev "DarkPower"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dark Wood
=========

   Dangerous undead trees similar in ability to the shadow wood but more
indiscriminate in what it attacks.

   The trees are controlled by the computer and will attack absolutely
anything nearby except other undeads.  Up to 6 trees may be cast.


@EndNode

@Node "DeadRevenge" "Chaos.Guide/DeadRevenge"
@Next "DeathBringer"
@Prev "DarkWood"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dead Revenge
============

   This extremely rare spell allows a wizard to haunt the opposition
even after death.  When a wizard protected with Dead Revenge is killed a
generator appears in the place where the wizard was killed.  The
generator will produce creatures for the player.  Furthermore, any
generators owned by the killed wizard will live on and continue to be
under the control of the dead wizard!

   Thus a player who is killed while possessing the Dead Revenge
powerup will still have an influence in the game, at least until all
his generators are each individually killed.


@EndNode

@Node "DeathBringer" "Chaos.Guide/DeathBringer"
@Next "DelacroixsDecloaker"
@Prev "DeadRevenge"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Death Bringer
=============

   A powerful spell which indiscriminately strikes down one creature on
the board.  Wizards are immune to the powerful magic used in this
spell, but creations of your own wizard are not.


@EndNode

@Node "DelacroixsDecloaker" "Chaos.Guide/DelacroixsDecloaker"
@Next "Demon"
@Prev "DeathBringer"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Delacroix's Decloaker
=====================

   Delacroix's Decloaker will blast the entire world with an
indescriminate wave of decloaking energy.  Thus everything and everyone
will immediately become uncloaked.


@EndNode

@Node "Demon" "Chaos.Guide/Demon"
@Next "DemonicTouch"
@Prev "DelacroixsDecloaker"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Demon
=====

   The demon is the most feared of all creatures.  They are incredibly
strong, exceptionally intelligent, and designed for combat.  Anything
less than a vampire best keep well clear of a demon.

   Magic is the best approach in dispelling a demon, but even this is a
difficult task.  Thankfully, demons are very rare.


@EndNode

@Node "DemonicTouch" "Chaos.Guide/DemonicTouch"
@Next "DemonicTouchBeam"
@Prev "Demon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Demonic Touch
=============

   Allows a wizard to call upon evil incarnate to instill a long term
fear in a chosen target.  The recipient will no longer be able fight
effectively, even if it previously received advanced combat training.
Indeed, the target can only regain combat ability via subsequent
retraining in combat.


@EndNode

@Node "DemonicTouchBeam" "Chaos.Guide/DemonicTouchBeam"
@Next "Depth"
@Prev "DemonicTouch"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Demonic Touch Beam
==================

   Causes your wizard to emit a beam of Demonic Touch.  This beam
affects your own creatures as well as your enemies.

   Everything in the chosen direction will have its combat reduced to 0.


@EndNode

@Node "Depth" "Chaos.Guide/Depth"
@Next "Derro"
@Prev "DemonicTouchBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Depth
=====

   Allows all spells (except creatures) to be cast with infinite range
and without line of sight.  This is a very desirable spell because it
enables a wizard to cast lightning bolts and similar weapons at any
opponent.

   Inanimate objects like trees, walls, growths and wasp nests can also
be cast in this manner.


@EndNode

@Node "Derro" "Chaos.Guide/Derro"
@Next "DestroyWall"
@Prev "Depth"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Derro
=====

   The derro are a degenerate race of metallic complexion.  Their
origin is uncertain.  Their stronghold is in subterranean realms and
they are not commonly seen above ground.

   Their style of fighting is not particularly suited to open combat
but they are persistent and not easily toppled.


@EndNode

@Node "DestroyWall" "Chaos.Guide/DestroyWall"
@Next "Devastation"
@Prev "Derro"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Destroy Wall
============

   When cast this spell destroys every piece of wall in the world by
causing localized matter disturbances in areas containing walls.  This
spell is only available through meditation.


@EndNode

@Node "Devastation" "Chaos.Guide/Devastation"
@Next "DireWolf"
@Prev "DestroyWall"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Devastation
===========

   When you are tired of the current battles cast this spell for a clean
start.  This spell essentially wipes the slate clean.  Everything except
wizards and generators is instantly destroyed.  Even mounted wizards
will be exposed.  However, this spell should be used with some caution.
It is best to use this spell when you have several good creatures on
your spell list with which you can repopulate the world after the
devastation.

   The use of this spell is bound to cause outrage on the part of other
wizards, which is all the more reason to use it.  The mechanism of this
spell has never been properly explained, but wizards known to have cast
it speak of a euphoric state of mind immediately after the devastation.


@EndNode

@Node "DireWolf" "Chaos.Guide/DireWolf"
@Next "Discard"
@Prev "Devastation"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dire Wolf
=========

   A huge variety of the normal wolf.  Single wolves are not very
useful but if collected into a group of about six or used in
conjunction with other species the dire wolf can be very useful.  They
can hear 2x as far as they can see and they can smell 3x as far as they
can see.  Wolves are scavengers.


@EndNode

@Node "Discard" "Chaos.Guide/Discard"
@Next "Disection"
@Prev "DireWolf"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Discard
=======

   A powerful magical spell which burrows into the minds of wizards and
tampers with their memory.  Its usual effect is temporary amnesia, and
the wizard will find most spells have suspiciously disappeared.

   These spells will eventually return, sometimes after a single turn.
A single invocation will induce this effect in all other wizards.


@EndNode

@Node "Disection" "Chaos.Guide/Disection"
@Next "Disrupt"
@Prev "Discard"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Disection
=========

   Causes a virtual knife to pass through the entire world.  All objects
including wizards and generators will feel its presence.  It is like
half the life force of the world is drained away in an instant.  It is
known to cause enfeeblement, nausea, and general light headedness.

   At the conclusion of the spell all objects (including those of the
caster) will be at half strength.  Creatures with wound recovery will
eventually heal, but for others the damage is irreversible.  The end
result is that for several turns afterwards kills will be a lot easier
to make.


@EndNode

@Node "Disrupt" "Chaos.Guide/Disrupt"
@Next "DitzyBlonde"
@Prev "Disection"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Disrupt
=======

   This spell causes a momentary lapse of vision in all enemy
creatures.  It can prove fatal to weak minded creatures and causes
permanent damage to the cerebral cortex of those that survive.

   This spell does not affect growths, inanimate objects or scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "DitzyBlonde" "Chaos.Guide/DitzyBlonde"
@Next "Double"
@Prev "Disrupt"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ditzy Blonde
============

   The Ditzy Blonde spell will cause the target to turn into a ditzy
blonde.

   Their intelligence will be set to 2. :)


@EndNode

@Node "Double" "Chaos.Guide/Double"
@Next "DragonNest"
@Prev "DitzyBlonde"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Double
======

   This is a sought after spell which gives the wizard the ability to
make two attempts with each subsequent spell, for a limited time.  It
is most valuable near the start of the game when building your forces.

   You cannot double a spell which grants multiple attempts.


@EndNode

@Node "DragonNest" "Chaos.Guide/DragonNest"
@Next "Drain"
@Prev "Double"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dragon Nest
===========

   This is a like the general purpose generator but is somewhat weaker
and only produces a limited number of races.  It is capable of
generating most of the dragon species.

   Casting such a generator will ensure that you always have a fresh
supply of strong creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "Drain" "Chaos.Guide/Drain"
@Next "DreadElf"
@Prev "DragonNest"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Drain
=====

   A powerful spell that wearies all the opposition.  All the opposition
creatures will feel inexplicably tired and will not feel like moving
very far.


@EndNode

@Node "DreadElf" "Chaos.Guide/DreadElf"
@Next "Drelb"
@Prev "Drain"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dread Elf
=========

   Not all elves are equal.  The dread elf is an elf who by previous
feats has high status among all elves.  They benefit greatly from this
revered status and always carry the very best bows.  Their extensive
battle experience makes them much more hardy than the usual elves.


@EndNode

@Node "Drelb" "Chaos.Guide/Drelb"
@Next "DualEarthbind"
@Prev "DreadElf"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Drelb
=====

   The drelb is very difficult to distinguish from a standard ghost.
The touch of a drelb is chilling to mortal flesh, more so than that of
the ghost, but they are spiritually weaker than the ghost.


@EndNode

@Node "DualEarthbind" "Chaos.Guide/DualEarthbind"
@Next "Eagle"
@Prev "Drelb"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Dual Earthbind
==============

   The target of this spell loses their wings and can no longer fly.
This has no effect on movement points.  2 attempts are granted.


@EndNode

@Node "Eagle" "Chaos.Guide/Eagle"
@Next "EarthElemental"
@Prev "DualEarthbind"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Eagle
=====

   The eagle can attack from great distances and move with extreme
agility.  Most land-ridden creatures have trouble defending an aerial
attack by an eagle.  Other birds such as the vulture and the falcon can
give the eagle a testing fight.  The Eagle has excellent eyesight.


@EndNode

@Node "EarthElemental" "Chaos.Guide/EarthElemental"
@Next "Earthquake"
@Prev "Eagle"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Earth Elemental
===============

   A muddy concoction from the depths of the earth, the earth elemental
is incredibly strong and is shunned by living creatures.

   Its destruction normally results in a strong earthquake.


@EndNode

@Node "Earthquake" "Chaos.Guide/Earthquake"
@Next "EarthquakeShield"
@Prev "EarthElemental"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Earthquake
==========

   A destructive movement of the ground initiated by the wizard or
resulting from the death of an earth elemental.  The earthquake will
instantly kill any creature in its path.  It will also crumble walls
and cause other damage.

   There is no way to stop its damage.


@EndNode

@Node "EarthquakeShield" "Chaos.Guide/EarthquakeShield"
@Next "EideticXenogenocide"
@Prev "Earthquake"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Earthquake Shield
=================

   A special shield only for the wizard, to permanently protect the
wizard from being killed by an earthquake.


@EndNode

@Node "EideticXenogenocide" "Chaos.Guide/EideticXenogenocide"
@Next "Elephant"
@Prev "EarthquakeShield"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Eidetic Xenogenocide
====================

   Eidetic Xenogenocide kills all enemy forces that have perfect Eidetic
Memory.

   This normally includes Elephants, Memory Masters, Memory Mages and
perhaps others.


@EndNode

@Node "Elephant" "Chaos.Guide/Elephant"
@Next "ElfBoots"
@Prev "EideticXenogenocide"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Elephant
========

   The elephant is very strong and attacks with its trunk and by
stomping.  Wizards are not normally permitted to ride elephants.  The
strength of the elephant makes it useful for attacking several
opponents simultaneously.

   The Elephant has perfect Eidetic Memory and will always remember
what is under the object in any square on the board.


@EndNode

@Node "ElfBoots" "Chaos.Guide/ElfBoots"
@Next "Elm"
@Prev "Elephant"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Elf Boots
=========

   A pair of boots made by some very learned elves.  They are a perfect
fit for your wizard and will make your wizard one of the most agile
creatures on the board.


@EndNode

@Node "Elm" "Chaos.Guide/Elm"
@Next "EmeraldDragon"
@Prev "ElfBoots"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Elm
===

   A rock and stock standard elm tree, great to sit under and listen to
the birds, just provides a little variety to the scenery.


@EndNode

@Node "EmeraldDragon" "Chaos.Guide/EmeraldDragon"
@Next "EncumberanceBeam"
@Prev "Elm"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Emerald Dragon
==============

   The emerald dragon is a battle hardened green dragon.  They have
exceptional combat ability.

   Such a creature is normally only available by having a green dragon
successfully make seven kills.


@EndNode

@Node "EncumberanceBeam" "Chaos.Guide/EncumberanceBeam"
@Next "Exophagy"
@Prev "EmeraldDragon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Encumberance Beam
=================

   Causes your wizard to emit a Beam of Encumberance which will drain 3
points of maneuverability from EVERYTHING in the chosen direction.  If
the target does not have at least 3 points of maneuver then the beam
causes 6 life points of damage for every maneuver point less than 3.

   This beam does not affect scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "Exophagy" "Chaos.Guide/Exophagy"
@Next "Exorcise"
@Prev "EncumberanceBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Exophagy
========

   Exophagy is the act of eating your enemies alive.  Yummy.

   Half of the damage you inflict in hand-to-hand combat will be added
to your life force.


@EndNode

@Node "Exorcise" "Chaos.Guide/Exorcise"
@Next "EyeforanEye"
@Prev "Exophagy"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Exorcise
========

   Exorcism is used to remove an evil presence but is not always
successful.  Line of sight is not required.  It can only be applied to
undead objects.

   The chosen subject will suffer 6 points of damage to its magical
resistance.


@EndNode

@Node "EyeforanEye" "Chaos.Guide/EyeforanEye"
@Next "Falcon"
@Prev "Exorcise"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Eye for an Eye
==============

   Gives special coverage to all your creations.  Should any of your
creations be killed or otherwise destroyed in combat then the killer
will also be struck dead.  The effect lasts for 2 kills and is
cumulative with multiple Eye for an Eye spells.  Thus if you have
triple and cast this spell the effect will last for 6 kills.


@EndNode

@Node "Falcon" "Chaos.Guide/Falcon"
@Next "Faun"
@Prev "EyeforanEye"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Falcon
======

   Falcons are very swift and can cross the longer axis of the visible
world in just three moves.  Because of this incredible range the falcon
is most useful for mounting long range aerial assaults and its
excellent eyesight makes it invaluable for long-range reconaissance.

   A falcon can only be granted through meditation.


@EndNode

@Node "Faun" "Chaos.Guide/Faun"
@Next "Feeble"
@Prev "Falcon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Faun
====

   The faun, or satyr as they are sometimes known, is a highly
intelligent creature with a high magical resistance.  They are rather
slow and not particularly skilled in combat but have a fair chance of
escaping from a conflict if desired.  Unfortunately, once wounded they
cannot heal themselves.

   If Agent Casting is enabled then on any given turn there is a 5%
chance that the faun will cast a sleep spell on an opponent.


@EndNode

@Node "Feeble" "Chaos.Guide/Feeble"
@Next "Fir"
@Prev "Faun"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Feeble
======

   Enfeeblement will cause the target to become so feeble that its life
will be reduced to 4 and its movement will be reduced to 1. All its
other stats will be reduced to 2.

   Recovery rates are not affected.


@EndNode

@Node "Fir" "Chaos.Guide/Fir"
@Next "Fire"
@Prev "Feeble"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Fir
===

   A plain and normal fir tree.  It has no special effects so don't
bother trying to find any.


@EndNode

@Node "Fire" "Chaos.Guide/Fire"
@Next "FireBat"
@Prev "Fir"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Fire
====

   Fire is very dangerous once conjured.  A fire continues to grow
until the conjurer is killed or until it is put out by other means.
Fires can burn any creature, living or undead or dead, or any wizard
not possessing a fire shield.  Fires even burn the creatures of the
conjurer and can even burn the conjurer.

   Fires can also burn down castles, citadels and even walls, although
this usually takes considerable time. The destructive ability of a fire
exceeds that of any creature including dragons and vampires. Fire can
be put out by active effort of creatures, each cell of fire has a
energy comparable to that of a faun or troll.


@EndNode

@Node "FireBat" "Chaos.Guide/FireBat"
@Next "FireDemon"
@Prev "Fire"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Fire Bat
========

   A bat which has been influenced by the underworld.  Their
constitution is similar to that of the imp, but they are not able to
attack full fledged undeads.


@EndNode

@Node "FireDemon" "Chaos.Guide/FireDemon"
@Next "FireElemental"
@Prev "FireBat"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Fire Demon
==========

   The fire demon is even more deadly than the standard demon.  They are
incredibly strong, exceptionally intelligent, and designed for combat.
In addition to the powers of the standard demon they can lash out with
their forked tongue.

   Thankfully, they are exceptionally rare.


@EndNode

@Node "FireElemental" "Chaos.Guide/FireElemental"
@Next "FireShield"
@Prev "FireDemon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Fire Elemental
==============

   A powerful creature possessing many of the properties of a real fire.
Living creatures shun the fire elemental and will not attack it, as it
appears to them to be an undead.  Such elementals are best disposed
using magic.

   However, even in death the fire elemental is a menace as it leaves
behind a real fire.


@EndNode

@Node "FireShield" "Chaos.Guide/FireShield"
@Next "Fireball"
@Prev "FireElemental"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Fire Shield
===========

   The fire shield can only be used by the wizard.  The fire shield
gives a wizard immunity from fire, but not from dragon breath, or heat
orientated magical weapons like magic bolts.

   Once cast it is unlikely the fire shield will ever become damaged.


@EndNode

@Node "Fireball" "Chaos.Guide/Fireball"
@Next "FleshtoStone"
@Prev "FireShield"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Fireball
========

   This spell causes the wizard to emit a ball of fire which will cause
magical damage and/or physical damage as the excess damage caused to the
magical resistance is transfered to the life force at a 10:1 ratio.

   Anything can be shot provided it is in range and line of sight is
available.  Be careful not to shoot your own creations.


@EndNode

@Node "FleshtoStone" "Chaos.Guide/FleshtoStone"
@Next "FloatingEye"
@Prev "Fireball"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Flesh to Stone
==============

   This spell will petrify any creature by transforming its flesh to
stone.

   The creature who is targetted by this powerful spell will instantly
become an inanimate object.


@EndNode

@Node "FloatingEye" "Chaos.Guide/FloatingEye"
@Next "Flood"
@Prev "FleshtoStone"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Floating Eye
============

   An unusual creature with the appearance of a floating human eye.
The eye induces a hypnotic trance in its enemies but is not
particularly strong.


@EndNode

@Node "Flood" "Chaos.Guide/Flood"
@Next "FloodShield"
@Prev "FloatingEye"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Flood
=====

   A flood behaves like a fire but tends to be short-lived.  That is, a
flood will often dissipate within two turns.

   Any creature, living or undead, may be drowned as a result of a
flood.  Flood can also damage creatures belonging to the casting wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "FloodShield" "Chaos.Guide/FloodShield"
@Next "Fly"
@Prev "Flood"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Flood Shield
============

   A special shield, only available for the wizard, which protects the
wizard from drowning in floods.

   Once a wizard gains a flood shield it is unlikely to ever become
damaged.


@EndNode

@Node "Fly" "Chaos.Guide/Fly"
@Next "ForceWall"
@Prev "FloodShield"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Fly
===

   The target of this spell is given wings and can fly.  This has no
effect on movement points.

   2 attempts are granted.


@EndNode

@Node "ForceWall" "Chaos.Guide/ForceWall"
@Next "Free"
@Prev "Fly"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Force Wall
==========

   It would take some serious magic to get one of these onto your spell
list.  In fact, thus far, no wizard has ever succeeded in getting a
Force Wall onto his spell list.  These walls are just about impossible
to obtain and are damn near indestructable.

   Many military complexes and dungeons have been built from these
walls for exactly these reasons.


@EndNode

@Node "Free" "Chaos.Guide/Free"
@Next "FreeAll"
@Prev "ForceWall"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Free
====

   This spell allows the wizard to liberate one creature.  The selected
creature immediately becomes an independent.

   If cast on an independent creature, the creature will go into a
trance.


@EndNode

@Node "FreeAll" "Chaos.Guide/FreeAll"
@Next "Freeze"
@Prev "Free"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Free All
========

   Causes every creature on the board to become an independent.  This
is a useful spell if your opponents have guarded themselves well.

   It is guaranteed to get all the wizards running scared.


@EndNode

@Node "Freeze" "Chaos.Guide/Freeze"
@Next "Generator"
@Prev "FreeAll"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Freeze
======

   A powerful spell that will temporarily cause disorder among all
creations of the chosen target.

   The enemy attacked will be unable to move or partake in combat for
the duration of the round, although you may remain engaged if in combat.


@EndNode

@Node "Generator" "Chaos.Guide/Generator"
@Next "Ghast"
@Prev "Freeze"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Generator
=========

   The generator spell allows a wizard to cast a generator identical in
appearance and operation to those used by the independent creatures.
This spell is only available by meditation.  It is unlikely that you
will ever get one of these spells.

   Like the independent generator, this generator will randomly produce
creatures belonging to the casting wizard, but unlike independent
creatures, once created the wizard takes responsibility for their
movement.

   Once cast the generator is essentially eternal.


@EndNode

@Node "Ghast" "Chaos.Guide/Ghast"
@Next "Ghost"
@Prev "Generator"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ghast
=====

   Ghasts are akin to ghouls in both appearance and abilities.  They
are most useful in blocking the onslaught from living creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "Ghost" "Chaos.Guide/Ghost"
@Next "Ghoul"
@Prev "Ghast"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ghost
=====

   The ghost is the spirit of a deceased evil human.  Ghosts can fly
but do not move particularly quickly.  Any ghost is best avoided by
living creatures but ghosts have a fair chance of being destroyed if
attacked by other undead creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "Ghoul" "Chaos.Guide/Ghoul"
@Next "GiantBeetle"
@Prev "Ghost"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ghoul
=====

   Once a human, these undeads now feed on others.  Ghouls are terribly
cunning, despite their low intelligence.


@EndNode

@Node "GiantBeetle" "Chaos.Guide/GiantBeetle"
@Next "GiantRat"
@Prev "Ghoul"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Giant Beetle
============

   The giant beetle is a pesky creature that does a good job of
hindering an enemy onslaught until more powerful defenders can arrive.
A giant beetle has an excellent chance of escaping conflict as it is
very agile.

   Giant beetles are easily killed by even the weakest of creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "GiantRat" "Chaos.Guide/GiantRat"
@Next "GiantSpider"
@Prev "GiantBeetle"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Giant Rat
=========

   The giant rat, or super rat, is a quick and evasive creature with
minimal intelligence and magical resistance.  The giant rat is a danger
to orcs, horses, elves, halflings, beetles, goblins and ogres but is
only a minor hinderance to other creatures.  Rats are superb scavengers.

   The bite of the giant rat is poisonous.


@EndNode

@Node "GiantSpider" "Chaos.Guide/GiantSpider"
@Next "GlobalThermonuclearWar"
@Prev "GiantRat"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Giant Spider
============

   A menacing hinderance to the opposition.  Although unlikely to be
fatal to any opposition the spider takes some effort to kill.

   This spider will also lay web as it moves. This spider eats scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "GlobalThermonuclearWar" "Chaos.Guide/GlobalThermonuclearWar"
@Next "Goblin"
@Prev "GiantSpider"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Global Thermonuclear War
========================

   This spell plunges the whole world into a horrific war.  All
alliances are immediately dissolved.  The caster of this spell is given
2 Nukes.  Every other player is given 1 Nuke.

   Can anything survive this?


@EndNode

@Node "Goblin" "Chaos.Guide/Goblin"
@Next "GoblinBomb"
@Prev "GlobalThermonuclearWar"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Goblin
======

   No campaign is complete without a goblin.  The goblin is among the
better fighters of the common bipedal living species.  The goblin can
fight as well as the ogre but is slightly weaker in its defence.


@EndNode

@Node "GoblinBomb" "Chaos.Guide/GoblinBomb"
@Next "GoldenDragon"
@Prev "Goblin"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Goblin Bomb
===========

   No campaign is complete without a goblin.  The goblin is among the
better fighters of the common bipedal living species.  The goblin can
fight as well as the ogre but is slightly weaker in its defence.

   This goblin carries a grenade and upon its death the goblin releases
the grenade which subsequently explodes causing damage to all adjacent
cells.


@EndNode

@Node "GoldenDragon" "Chaos.Guide/GoldenDragon"
@Next "GooeyBlob"
@Prev "GoblinBomb"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Golden Dragon
=============

   A very intelligent creature that rules amongst the good living
species with the exception of the immensely rare platinum dragon.  The
golden dragon can fight in a similar vein as the stone giant but has
the gift of fire breathing and flight which makes it extremely deadly
to any creature or wizard that attracts its attention.

   The golden dragon can kill some of the lesser dragons.


@EndNode

@Node "GooeyBlob" "Chaos.Guide/GooeyBlob"
@Next "Gorilla"
@Prev "GoldenDragon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Gooey Blob
==========

   Gooey blob is particularly useful and can be conjured some distance
from the wizard provided there is line of sight.  The gooey blob then
grows much like a fire does.  No part of the gooey blob can be moved.
Although the gooey blob has no intelligence it will never harm its
master or any of its master's creatures.

   However, the gooey blob quickly grows over enemy creatures
preventing them from moving but not actually killing them. Buried
creatures can be recovered by killing the gooey blob on them.

   Rescued creatures will have half their initial life remaining after
being uncovered no matter how much they had when they were buried, so
their life on recovery can be more or less than what it was when they
were buried. If an enemy wizard succumbs to the blob that wizard dies.


@EndNode

@Node "Gorilla" "Chaos.Guide/Gorilla"
@Next "GravitySphere"
@Prev "GooeyBlob"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Gorilla
=======

   Gorillas are a good middle of the road animal and are a worthy
adversary for most bipedal living creatures such as trolls, ogres, and
goblins.  The more violent animals such as the lion and grizzly bear
can kill a gorilla.

   The gorilla has only mediocre intelligence but fights with vigour.


@EndNode

@Node "GravitySphere" "Chaos.Guide/GravitySphere"
@Next "GrayElf"
@Prev "Gorilla"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Gravity Sphere
==============

   Causes the wizard to create a dense sphere of neutrons, much like a
miniature neutron star, which causes the gravity to increase
exponentially.  Indeed, gravity becomes so strong that flying movement
becomes impossible.

   All creatures which can normally fly will be forced to move like any
other creature. The sphere will eventually decay and normal flight can
then resume.

   A typical instance will last for 6 turns, however, if several
wizards cast this spell in succession the delay could be much longer.


@EndNode

@Node "GrayElf" "Chaos.Guide/GrayElf"
@Next "GreenDragon"
@Prev "GravitySphere"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Gray Elf
========

   The gray elf is very similar to the more common wood elf but posesses
accelerated healing ability.  They carry the best bows and are able to
make accurate shots over a greater distance than Wood Elves.


@EndNode

@Node "GreenDragon" "Chaos.Guide/GreenDragon"
@Next "GreenOoze"
@Prev "GrayElf"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Green Dragon
============

   The green dragon is the weakest species of dragon, having a strength
similar to that of a crocodile.  Of course, the green dragon is far more
useful than the crocodile, as it can move further and more importantly
can use a breath weapon.

   The breath weapon consists of chlorine gas and is quite deadly. The
dragon will recover from injuries but not as quickly as red and golden
dragons do.


@EndNode

@Node "GreenOoze" "Chaos.Guide/GreenOoze"
@Next "GrimReaper"
@Prev "GreenDragon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Green Ooze
==========

   Green ooze is very similar to the gooey blob and it grows in the same
manner.  The green ooze cannot be moved in the same way as you move your
other creatures.  Instead it grows on its own accord.

   Any creature which succumbs to the ooze can be recovered by killing
the ooze on the creature concerned.


@EndNode

@Node "GrimReaper" "Chaos.Guide/GrimReaper"
@Next "GrizzlyBear"
@Prev "GreenOoze"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Grim Reaper
===========

   This Spell summons Death to Earth and binds him to the control of the
casting wizard.  The Grim Reaper moves the way you command, but charges
his toll in the form of the lives of those who surround him, no matter
which party they belong to.

   If unwisely moved, he will also take the life of his master, which
allows him to leave our world at last.


@EndNode

@Node "GrizzlyBear" "Chaos.Guide/GrizzlyBear"
@Next "Gryphon"
@Prev "GrimReaper"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Grizzly Bear
============

   The grizzly bear is an extremely powerful animal capable of killing
a lion or a brown bear.  Like most aggressive animals the grizzly bear
has a low magical resistance.

   If reincarnated the grizzly bear becomes an ogre mage.


@EndNode

@Node "Gryphon" "Chaos.Guide/Gryphon"
@Next "Halfling"
@Prev "GrizzlyBear"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Gryphon
=======

   A large flying beast which can be ridden by the wizard who conjured
it.  The gryphon has a good stamina and magical resistance but is not
particularly agile.  The gryphon is not a particularly skilled fighter
but can move a considerable distance enabling a mounted wizard to
quickly escape from difficult situations.


@EndNode

@Node "Halfling" "Chaos.Guide/Halfling"
@Next "HandGrenade"
@Prev "Gryphon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Halfling
========

   These little guys are extremely magic resistant.  The halfling is
typically a hard-working, orderly, and peaceful citizen similar to a
human, although much smaller.  They usually fight with swords although
some have been known to carry bows.  While they fight well, and with
determination, they have little stamina and quickly become exhausted in
battle.


@EndNode

@Node "HandGrenade" "Chaos.Guide/HandGrenade"
@Next "Harpy"
@Prev "Halfling"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Hand Grenade
============

   The Hand Grenade can be cast up to 3 squares away and does not
require line of sight.

   It inflicts 14 points of damage to the target square and 7 points to
each adjacent square.


@EndNode

@Node "Harpy" "Chaos.Guide/Harpy"
@Next "Haste"
@Prev "HandGrenade"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Harpy
=====

   The harpy is a cross between a vulture and a female human.  Harpies
are fast and can mount aerial attacks thereby avoiding direct
engagement.  Using vulture claws the harpy can rip into the hide of
most beasts and can outfly would be attackers.

   Unfortunately, the harpy possesses relatively poor eyesight and
smell.


@EndNode

@Node "Haste" "Chaos.Guide/Haste"
@Next "Haunt"
@Prev "Harpy"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Haste
=====

   A spell used to urge your creations on to greater speed.  It boosts
the speed of all your creations by one unit.

   This is particularly useful after another player has cast Drain.


@EndNode

@Node "Haunt" "Chaos.Guide/Haunt"
@Next "Heal"
@Prev "Haste"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Haunt
=====

   A variant of the spectre.  Haunts are very difficult to control and
will occassionally switch sides for no apparent reason.

   It follows that haunts should be used with extreme caution.


@EndNode

@Node "Heal" "Chaos.Guide/Heal"
@Next "HiddenHorror"
@Prev "Haunt"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Heal
====

   The Heal spell heals any 1 creature.

   It does not require line of sight and works over the entire world.


@EndNode

@Node "HiddenHorror" "Chaos.Guide/HiddenHorror"
@Next "Hide"
@Prev "Heal"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Hidden Horror
=============

   For all intents and purposes this is a halfling with a singular
important difference.  Upon its death the hidden horror becomes a red
dragon (unless it is set to reincarnate, in which case it becomes a
golden dragon).

   The halfling is typically a hard-working, orderly, and peaceful
citizen similar to a human, although much smaller. They usually fight
with swords although some have been known to carry bows. While they
fight well, and with determination, they have little stamina and
quickly become exhausted in battle.


@EndNode

@Node "Hide" "Chaos.Guide/Hide"
@Next "HigherDevil"
@Prev "HiddenHorror"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Hide
====

   Causes your wizard to disappear from the game for some time
(typically about 5 rounds).  During this time you will be unable to do
anything, you will not be able to cast creatures.  However, you will be
able to move any creatures you have left on the board.

   The spell is most useful when your wizard is in a tight spot. You
reappear at a random position.


@EndNode

@Node "HigherDevil" "Chaos.Guide/HigherDevil"
@Next "Hippocrates"
@Prev "Hide"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Higher Devil
============

   A higher devil is summoned from the pits of hell by the wizard.  They
somewhat resemble demons in their appearance and abilities and are
generally shunned by other creatures including undeads.

   Once cast the devil is very faithful to the wizard and will
obediently carry out any tasks set with no complaint.


@EndNode

@Node "Hippocrates" "Chaos.Guide/Hippocrates"
@Next "Horror"
@Prev "HigherDevil"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Hippocrates
===========

   Hippocrates is the legendary Greek physician.  He automatically
heals all friendly things adjacent to him.  And he can use his "attack"
to heal anyone, even an enemy.


@EndNode

@Node "Horror" "Chaos.Guide/Horror"
@Next "Horse"
@Prev "Hippocrates"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Horror
======

   A powerful form of sorcery which enables a creature to replicate
itself upon death by combat.


@EndNode

@Node "Horse" "Chaos.Guide/Horse"
@Next "Hybsil"
@Prev "Horror"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Horse
=====

   The horse may be ridden by the wizard and is useful in this regard
for carrying the wizard out of a tight spot.

   The horse, however, should avoid conflicts and magical attack
because it is not particularly suited to combat.


@EndNode

@Node "Hybsil" "Chaos.Guide/Hybsil"
@Next "Hydra"
@Prev "Horse"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Hybsil
======

   An antelope centaur appearing in similar form to a centaur.  They are
weaker than a true centaur but fire poisonned arrows.

   The hybsil can also be ridden by the wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "Hydra" "Chaos.Guide/Hydra"
@Next "Hyperclone"
@Prev "Hybsil"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Hydra
=====

   These slow moving multiheaded beasts are very hard to kill and are
extremely apt at fighting.  They are not particularly stupid either but
have great trouble escaping from a conflict once initiated.

   The hydra is strong enough to hold most undeads at bay for several
turns.


@EndNode

@Node "Hyperclone" "Chaos.Guide/Hyperclone"
@Next "IceBreath"
@Prev "Hydra"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Hyperclone
==========

   Hyperclone is an extremely potent spell which will replicate every
single creature controlled by your wizard.  Each clone will be
functionally equivalent to the original.  Clearly this spell is most
effective when you already have a large number of creatures.

   Hyperclone will not replicate your wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "IceBreath" "Chaos.Guide/IceBreath"
@Next "Imp"
@Prev "Hyperclone"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ice Breath
==========

   This spell causes the wizard to breathe out an icy beam.  This beam
can only be resisted by magic.  Any creature hit by the icy beam will
have its magical resistance lowered by 2 points with the excess damage
transfered to its life force at a 10:1 ratio.

   Thus, very weak creatures are likely to die of hypothermia.


@EndNode

@Node "Imp" "Chaos.Guide/Imp"
@Next "Inanimage"
@Prev "IceBreath"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Imp
===

   The imp is a very low form of devil and is not greatly feared.
Although the imp is not undead, it can attack undeads with ease.


@EndNode

@Node "Inanimage" "Chaos.Guide/Inanimage"
@Next "Inanimatologist"
@Prev "Imp"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Inanimage
=========

   The Inanimage is what an Inanimatologist becomes after making 3
kills.  He can instantly reveal the stats of any inanimate object by
looking at its scroll.  He is fond of casting rocks and power walls.

   He can throw fireballs as well as an Ogre Mage and he also heals
friendly inanimate objects adjacent to himself.


@EndNode

@Node "Inanimatologist" "Chaos.Guide/Inanimatologist"
@Next "Inanimorphobiosis"
@Prev "Inanimage"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Inanimatologist
===============

   The Inanimatologist can instantly reveal the stats of any inanimate
object by looking at its scroll.  He is also fond of casting rocks and
power walls.


@EndNode

@Node "Inanimorphobiosis" "Chaos.Guide/Inanimorphobiosis"
@Next "Invert"
@Prev "Inanimatologist"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Inanimorphobiosis
=================

   Inanimorphobiosis is a more potent version of Stone to Flesh
designed by Professor Conwell to utilize the full power of advanced
scientific principles.  The spell name is derived from Inanimate +
morph "to change" + bio "life" + sis  "the act of".  So it means
literally, the act of changing from inanimate to living.

   The recipient inanimate object will become a creature under your
control and will be able to move at least 5 squares and attack with at
least 5 points of combat.


@EndNode

@Node "Invert" "Chaos.Guide/Invert"
@Next "IridiumHorse"
@Prev "Inanimorphobiosis"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Invert
======

   The invert spell causes strange fluctuations in the strength of
creatures.  Normally strong creatures will suddenly become very weak
and conversely weak creatures will become strong.

   The spell affects only the creatures of the selected target.


@EndNode

@Node "IridiumHorse" "Chaos.Guide/IridiumHorse"
@Next "IrvinesInvulnerability"
@Prev "Invert"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Iridium Horse
=============

   A extraordinarily rare super enhanced form of horse.  This spell is
even rarer than the powerful thundermare.  As a general rule this spell
does not appear on spell lists (you are about as likely to get a
generator on your spell list).  Under normal circumstances an irdium
horse only occurs when a thundermare kills a red, green, blue, or
golden dragon.

   The iridium horse is the ultimate in mounts. It is strong, swift, and
deadly in combat. Not only can it attack in similar vein to the
thundermare, but it also has a powerful iridium stare which affects
several statistics of the target simultaneously. The irdium horse also
freely attacks undeads even though it is not undead itself. The
nightmare pales in comparison to this awesome beast. Even demons are
known to be wary of this animal.

   The iridium horse represents the most powerful mount available and a
wizard fortunate enough to have an Iridium Horse commits an extreme
faux pas if he does not ride this beast.


@EndNode

@Node "IrvinesInvulnerability" "Chaos.Guide/IrvinesInvulnerability"
@Next "Jaguar"
@Prev "IridiumHorse"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Irvine's Invulnerability
========================

   Created by the ancient wizard Irvine to stave off the deadly attacks
of his arch-rival King Conwell who seems to have had a fondness for
catapulting cows at him when he wasn't looking.

   This spell uses extremely powerful but rather unstable magic to
render the caster invulnerable to any and all physical attacks. After
several turns the instability becomes too great and the spell
evaporates into nothingness.


@EndNode

@Node "Jaguar" "Chaos.Guide/Jaguar"
@Next "Jann"
@Prev "IrvinesInvulnerability"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Jaguar
======

   This jungle predator is very dangerous despite being slightly weaker
than the lion.  The jaguar can outrun a lion and can even match the
speed of some flying creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "Jann" "Chaos.Guide/Jann"
@Next "Joker"
@Prev "Jaguar"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Jann
====

   The weakest of the genies.  This genie is able to cause random
occurrences of orange jelly, gooey blob, and green ooze.  A jann can
also boil water and quench fires.


@EndNode

@Node "Joker" "Chaos.Guide/Joker"
@Next "JujuZombie"
@Prev "Jann"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Joker
=====

   A powerful spell that causes your entire spell list to be randomly
permuted.

   When the joker is used, the chances of getting rare and otherwise
impossible to obtain spells improves.


@EndNode

@Node "JujuZombie" "Chaos.Guide/JujuZombie"
@Next "Justice"
@Prev "Joker"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Juju Zombie
===========

   An extra powerful zombie that attacks a creature's magical resistance
rather than their life force.


@EndNode

@Node "Justice" "Chaos.Guide/Justice"
@Next "Kill"
@Prev "JujuZombie"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Justice
=======

   A spell which attempts to make a creature see the evil of its ways.
The feedback generated is often enough to kill the target.

   It can be applied to wizards, does not require line of sight and has
infinite range. 2 attempts are granted, each of which inflicts 3 points
of damage to the creature's magical resistance.


@EndNode

@Node "Kill" "Chaos.Guide/Kill"
@Next "KingCobra"
@Prev "Justice"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Kill
====

   An extremely potent spell only available by meditation.  The chosen
target, living or undead, will instantly drop dead.  The spell simply
switches off the creatures brain.

   Wizards are immune to its effects. Kills are best used on strong
undeads such as demons.


@EndNode

@Node "KingCobra" "Chaos.Guide/KingCobra"
@Next "Leopard"
@Prev "Kill"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

King Cobra
==========

   The king cobra has very little to recommend for it, aside from the
fact that its poisonous bite causes permanent damage to any victim
stupid enough to get close to it.

   Every creature is capable of killing a king cobra, even creatures as
low as bats, dire wolves, vultures, fauns, elves, and pegasii can kill
a king cobra in a single blow. The king cobra is also stupid, has
minimal magical resistance, and is sluggish. Assuming the cobra
survives an attack, it has a good chance of escaping the conflict.


@EndNode

@Node "Leopard" "Chaos.Guide/Leopard"
@Next "LesserDevil"
@Prev "KingCobra"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Leopard
=======

   This predator is very ferocious although not as strong as a lion.
They can outrun nearly any land-ridden creature and some flying
species.  The leopard offers considerable combat assistance to any
party.


@EndNode

@Node "LesserDevil" "Chaos.Guide/LesserDevil"
@Next "LethargyBeam"
@Prev "Leopard"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Lesser Devil
============

   A lesser devil is summoned from the pits of hell by the wizard.  They
somewhat resemble demons in their appearance and abilities and are
generally shunned by other creatures including undeads.

   Once cast, the devil is very faithful to the wizard and will
obediently carry out any task with no complaint.


@EndNode

@Node "LethargyBeam" "Chaos.Guide/LethargyBeam"
@Next "Level"
@Prev "LesserDevil"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Lethargy Beam
=============

   Causes your wizard to emit a Beam of Lethargy which will drain 3
points of movement from EVERYTHING in the chosen direction.  If the
target does not have at least 3 points of movement then the beam causes
6 life points of damage for every movement point less than 3.

   This beam does not affect scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "Level" "Chaos.Guide/Level"
@Next "Lich"
@Prev "LethargyBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Level
=====

   Improves your wizard's chances of getting unlikely and difficult
spells as bonus spells.  The effect is cumulative.  The more level
spells cast the better the chances of getting good spells.


@EndNode

@Node "Lich" "Chaos.Guide/Lich"
@Next "LichLord"
@Prev "Level"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Lich
====

   This spell can only be applied to creatures on your team.  The
creature concerned instantly becomes an undead but retains all its
current abilities.


@EndNode

@Node "LichLord" "Chaos.Guide/LichLord"
@Next "LifeDrainBeam"
@Prev "Lich"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Lich Lord
=========

   This spell is for the wizard.  If your wizard is killed in combat the
wizard is reinstated in the game as an undead.


@EndNode

@Node "LifeDrainBeam" "Chaos.Guide/LifeDrainBeam"
@Next "Lightning"
@Prev "LichLord"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Life Drain Beam
===============

   Causes your wizard to emit a Beam of Life Draining which will drain
16 points of life from EVERYTHING in the chosen direction except
scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "Lightning" "Chaos.Guide/Lightning"
@Next "Lion"
@Prev "LifeDrainBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Lightning
=========

   An easy spell which causes the wizard to emit a lightning bolt.  The
bolt can travel up to four squares provided there is line of sight.
Its magical and physical components will lower the magical resistance
of any creature struck by 2 points and transfer the excess damage to
its life force at a 10:1 ratio.

   For example, a creature with a magical resistance of 0 and a life
force of 15 will die as it would suffer 20 points of damage to its life
force.


@EndNode

@Node "Lion" "Chaos.Guide/Lion"
@Next "MagicAttack"
@Prev "Lightning"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Lion
====

   The lion is a ferocious beast once provoked and can take considerable
punishment from a foe.  The lion is amongst the faster of the
land-ridden creatures and has above-average intelligence.  The lion
comes into its own in combat as it is a very proficient attacker with a
good ability to escape conflicts when things are not going its way.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicAttack" "Chaos.Guide/MagicAttack"
@Next "MagicBolt"
@Prev "Lion"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Attack
============

   This spell can be cast on an enemy creature or wizard and will lower
the life force of the target by 10 points.

   This spell does not attack Magic Resistance.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicBolt" "Chaos.Guide/MagicBolt"
@Next "MagicBow"
@Prev "MagicAttack"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Bolt
==========

   A plain magical attack which works against any object.  If used on a
dead creature the corpse will be destroyed.  It will attack the magical
resistance of the chosen target and lower it by 2 points.  For each
magical resistance point under 2, the creature is inflicted 10 points
of damage to its life force.

   Therefore, this spell is best used against creatures with low magical
resistance.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicBow" "Chaos.Guide/MagicBow"
@Next "MagicCarpet"
@Prev "MagicBolt"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Bow
=========

   A magic bow which can only be given to the casting wizard.  The bow
will allow the wizard to shoot an arrow 6 squares each turn.  In
addition the wizard will be able to attack and shoot undeads.

   The bow can be used in conjunction with other magical weapons.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicCarpet" "Chaos.Guide/MagicCarpet"
@Next "MagicCastle"
@Prev "MagicBow"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Carpet
============

   The Magic Carpet is a flying mediation for the use of the wizard.  A
wizard mounted on a Magic Carpet can fly.

   As with any meditation object, each turn there is a chance that the
Magic Carpet will collapse and grant the wizard with a bonus spell.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicCastle" "Chaos.Guide/MagicCastle"
@Next "MagicGlass"
@Prev "MagicCarpet"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Castle
============

   The magic castle is functionally equivalent to the dark citadel.  It
provides a safe haven for the wizard, and a place for meditation.
There is a chance of the castle collapsing at each turn, if this should
happen while the wizard is inside, a new spell will be granted.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicGlass" "Chaos.Guide/MagicGlass"
@Next "MagicKnife"
@Prev "MagicCastle"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Glass
===========

   This spell allows the wizard to produce 4 pieces of magic glass.  To
the opposition the glass has the strength and consistency of a wall,
but to your own creatures the glass will allow line of sight and ranged
combat.

   It is the ideal substance behind which to locate creatures with
ranged combat or even to hide your wizard. One nice thing about this
spell is that you don't need Line of Sight to cast it.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicKnife" "Chaos.Guide/MagicKnife"
@Next "MagicShield"
@Prev "MagicGlass"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Knife
===========

   A knife for the use of the wizard that has magical properties
rendering it effective against undeads.

   May be used in conjunction with a magic sword or bow.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicShield" "Chaos.Guide/MagicShield"
@Next "MagicSword"
@Prev "MagicKnife"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Shield
============

   A shield which can be used to increase a creature's magical
resistance.  This quite frequent spell should be applied to your wizard
and your strong creatures.  The shield remains in force until damaged
by magical attack.

   Applying a shield to a creature with maximum magical resistance will
give enhanced protection.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicSword" "Chaos.Guide/MagicSword"
@Next "MagicWand"
@Prev "MagicShield"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Sword
===========

   A sword for the use of the wizard which increases the wizard's combat
ability.  The sword is magical and enables a wizard to attack undeads.

   The sword can be used in conjunction with other magical weapons.


@EndNode

@Node "MagicWand" "Chaos.Guide/MagicWand"
@Next "MagicWood"
@Prev "MagicSword"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Wand
==========

   Wow!  What a great spell!  Each Magic Wand increases your casting
range by 1 square cumulatively.  Any wizard who could somehow obtain 2
or 3 of these would be awesomely powerful.

   The Magic Wand increases the casting range of not only magical
spells, but of creatures too!


@EndNode

@Node "MagicWood" "Chaos.Guide/MagicWood"
@Next "ManaBattery"
@Prev "MagicWand"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Magic Wood
==========

   Magic wood is very useful even though it cannot fight like a shadow
wood.  The biggest boon of the magic wood is that a wizard may use such
a tree for meditation.  When the tree collapses the wizard occupying
the tree at the time is granted a new spell.

   Unlike castles the trees will not collapse unless occupied. The tree
also provides a wizard with shielding from the watchful eyes of the
independents. Magic trees can be destroyed by combat and some magical
weapons.

   Any wizard may make use of any magic tree provided it is not already
occupied. Each magic wood spell can produce up to 8 trees.


@EndNode

@Node "ManaBattery" "Chaos.Guide/ManaBattery"
@Next "Manticore"
@Prev "MagicWood"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mana Battery
============

   An energetic source of magical and psionic energy.  Any wizard
adjacent to such a battery will regularly gain new spells.  The battery
is long life and none are known to have ceased operation by natural
causes.

   Naturally, independent creatures tend to loathe these batteries, as
they invariably result in a worse life for the independents.


@EndNode

@Node "Manticore" "Chaos.Guide/Manticore"
@Next "Marid"
@Prev "ManaBattery"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Manticore
=========

   The manticore is one of the most powerful creatures which may be
ridden by a wizard.  The manticore has the advantage of being able to
fire spikes from its tail as well as take part in direct combat.  The
manticore also has a high magical resistance.

   The only drawback to the manticore is its small brain.


@EndNode

@Node "Marid" "Chaos.Guide/Marid"
@Next "Martyr"
@Prev "Manticore"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Marid
=====

   The most powerful genie.  A Marid is able to perform quite a number
of spells which are usually advantageous to the controlling wizard.

   If you can obtain a Marid then you should probably keep him a secure
position.


@EndNode

@Node "Martyr" "Chaos.Guide/Martyr"
@Next "MassMorph"
@Prev "Marid"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Martyr
======

   The death of this creature will be so emotional, traumatic, painful
and horrific that all your creatures will be angered into fighting more
fiercely than ever before!  All your creatures will gain +2 combat and
+1 move.

   Remember the martyr!  He must be avenged!


@EndNode

@Node "MassMorph" "Chaos.Guide/MassMorph"
@Next "MassPetrification"
@Prev "Martyr"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mass Morph
==========

   A powerful spell best cast on an enemy with many creations.  In
extreme circumstances, you might cast this spell on your own wizard.
Mass morph changes all of a player's creations, except generators, into
magic trees which can then be used for meditation by any player.

   No wizard, nor any wizard's mount is affected by this spell.


@EndNode

@Node "MassPetrification" "Chaos.Guide/MassPetrification"
@Next "MassResurrect"
@Prev "MassMorph"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mass Petrification
==================

   This spell is like Flesh to Stone except that it allows 3 attempts
over a very limited range.

   Extremely useful when you are surrounded by powerful enemy creatures
and are about to die.


@EndNode

@Node "MassResurrect" "Chaos.Guide/MassResurrect"
@Next "Materialize"
@Prev "MassPetrification"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mass Resurrect
==============

   A spell which brings all visible corpses back to life as standard
living beetles.

   While beetles are not particularly useful this spell does get rid of
all the corpses which are visible.


@EndNode

@Node "Materialize" "Chaos.Guide/Materialize"
@Next "Meddle"
@Prev "MassResurrect"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Materialize
===========

   Are you sick of battling with creatures from the astral planes?  Are
you tired of your living creatures being slaughtered wantonly by the
undead?  Then this is the spell for you.

   All undeads will instantly become living creatures attackable by all
creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "Meddle" "Chaos.Guide/Meddle"
@Next "MemoryMage"
@Prev "Materialize"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Meddle
======

   A wave of death passes over the land, followed by a rejuvination.
Some have likened it to a turning of the world.  The result is that all
creatures pass to their reincarnation.

   The usual result is a slight weakening of the world, since most
creature reincarnate downwards. An additional side effect is that all
creatures lose any current ability to reincarnate. Things which cannot
be reincarnated (like inanimate objects) are unaffected by this spell.


@EndNode

@Node "MemoryMage" "Chaos.Guide/MemoryMage"
@Next "MemoryMaster"
@Prev "Meddle"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Memory Mage
===========

   The Memory Mage has perfect Eidetic Memory and will always remember
what is under the object in any square on the board.

   The Memory Mage is a Memory Master who has been specially trained in
the art of fireball-throwing and healing.


@EndNode

@Node "MemoryMaster" "Chaos.Guide/MemoryMaster"
@Next "MeteorStorm"
@Prev "MemoryMage"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Memory Master
=============

   The Memory Master has perfect Eidetic Memory and will always
remember what is under the object in any square on the board.


@EndNode

@Node "MeteorStorm" "Chaos.Guide/MeteorStorm"
@Next "MightyOrc"
@Prev "MemoryMaster"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Meteor Storm
============

   Causes rocks to fall from the sky to random locations on the board.
Any creature hit by a rock is likely to be severely damaged often
resulting in death.


@EndNode

@Node "MightyOrc" "Chaos.Guide/MightyOrc"
@Next "MindFlayer"
@Prev "MeteorStorm"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mighty Orc
==========

   Every once in a while an orc is born unlike any other.  This is The
Mighty Orc.

   It is seriously pissed off and it loves to steal bows from elves.


@EndNode

@Node "MindFlayer" "Chaos.Guide/MindFlayer"
@Next "MinerWilly"
@Prev "MightyOrc"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mind Flayer
===========

   The tentacle arms of this happy looking killer suck the intellect of
nearby opponents.

   The mind flayer itself is very weak and will probably only make a
single attack before dying itself.


@EndNode

@Node "MinerWilly" "Chaos.Guide/MinerWilly"
@Next "Mnemicide"
@Prev "MindFlayer"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Miner Willy
===========

   A memorial to the greatest miner of all time.  Miner Willy of Jet
Set Willy and Manic Miner fame.  This brilliant edifice to Willy gives
extra kudos to your team since it shows you feel so confident in your
position as to have time to cast relatively weak spells.  However,
statue Willy is not entirely useless and he makes a useful obstruction.

   This spell is also a good choice for discarding.


@EndNode

@Node "Mnemicide" "Chaos.Guide/Mnemicide"
@Next "Mount"
@Prev "MinerWilly"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mnemicide
=========

   Mnemicide can kill any 1 thing that has perfect Eidetic Memory.  This
normally includes Elephants, Memory Masters, Memory Mages and perhaps
others.  Cannot be cast on wizards.


@EndNode

@Node "Mount" "Chaos.Guide/Mount"
@Next "MoveIt"
@Prev "Mnemicide"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mount
=====

   Works over the entire world and does not require line of sight.

   The recipient creature immediately becomes mountable and may be
mounted by the wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "MoveIt" "Chaos.Guide/MoveIt"
@Next "MudMan"
@Prev "Mount"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Move It
=======

   An order to your creations to make an extra move.  This spell is
useful when you want to quickly assert your dominance on the game.

   After each wizard has moved you will be given a second chance to
move all your creatures. The extra move will occur in the same round as
the spell is cast.


@EndNode

@Node "MudMan" "Chaos.Guide/MudMan"
@Next "MullacDeIrvine"
@Prev "MoveIt"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mud Man
=======

   A piece of animated mud, taking a vaguely humanoid form which bears a
resemblance to the earth elemental.

   They attack by hurling mud balls at their opponents and are not
easily damaged by swords or arrows.


@EndNode

@Node "MullacDeIrvine" "Chaos.Guide/MullacDeIrvine"
@Next "Mutate"
@Prev "MudMan"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mullac De Irvine
================

   Mullac De Irvine is also known as "The GrowthMaster".  He can
instantly recognize the stats of any growth by viewing its scroll.

   He is also fond of casting various growth-related spells.


@EndNode

@Node "Mutate" "Chaos.Guide/Mutate"
@Next "Necromancer"
@Prev "MullacDeIrvine"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Mutate
======

   An extremely potent spell, similar in function to Alter Reality, but
affecting every creature of a given player.

   The spell can be used on strong opposition to make it weak, or on
yourself if you have many weak creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "Necromancer" "Chaos.Guide/Necromancer"
@Next "Necropotence"
@Prev "Mutate"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Necromancer
===========

   A Necromancer is a wizard who specializes in Death Magic.  They
typically only cast Kill and Raise Dead spells.


@EndNode

@Node "Necropotence" "Chaos.Guide/Necropotence"
@Next "Neo-Otyugh"
@Prev "Necromancer"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Necropotence
============

   A magical spell that effectively blocks psionic forces for an
indeterminate amount of time.  Other wizards will be unable to cast
magic spells for a limited amount of time.  It will not prevent enemy
wizards from casting creatures.

   Your wizard, however, will be able to cast spells of both types. Some
wizards may regain the ability to cast magic spells after a single turn,
for other wizards this may take longer.


@EndNode

@Node "Neo-Otyugh" "Chaos.Guide/Neo-Otyugh"
@Next "NightoftheLivingDead"
@Prev "Necropotence"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Neo-Otyugh
==========

   A weird tripodal scavenger.  The neo-otyugh has three tentacle arms
one of which can lash out a considerable distance.

   They have a tough hide and can survive persistent attack.


@EndNode

@Node "NightoftheLivingDead" "Chaos.Guide/NightoftheLivingDead"
@Next "Nightmare"
@Prev "Neo-Otyugh"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Night of the Living Dead
========================

   Night of the Living Dead raises every corpse in the whole world into
a zombie under your control.


@EndNode

@Node "Nightmare" "Chaos.Guide/Nightmare"
@Next "NoGrow"
@Prev "NightoftheLivingDead"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Nightmare
=========

   Also known as a demon horse or hell horse, nightmares are creatures
from the lower planes.  They can, however, be ridden by the wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "NoGrow" "Chaos.Guide/NoGrow"
@Next "NoMount"
@Prev "Nightmare"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

No Grow
=======

   Works over the entire world and does not require line of sight.  Up
to 10 pieces of growth can be altered in such a way that they will stop
growing.

   They will lose their growth attribute and will also become inanimate.


@EndNode

@Node "NoMount" "Chaos.Guide/NoMount"
@Next "Nuke"
@Prev "NoGrow"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

No Mount
========

   Works over the entire world and does not require line of sight.  The
target creatures immediately become unmountable and may not be mounted
by a wizard.

   Up to 3 creatures may be made unmountable.


@EndNode

@Node "Nuke" "Chaos.Guide/Nuke"
@Next "Ogre"
@Prev "NoMount"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Nuke
====

   Nuke allows a wizard to invoke a local nuclear disturbance in a
chosen cell.  Anything in the cell will be instantly destroyed.  The
chosen cell will remain radioactive for the duration of the game.
Anything trying to enter or shoot into a radioactive cell also dies
instantly.

   Due to the magical protective aura surrounding a wizard, Nuke will
not succeed against a wizard or anything that a wizard is riding on or
meditating in. Thus a Nuke will succeed against a generator but will
fail against a horse being ridden by a wizard.

   Nukes can only be obtained by meditation.


@EndNode

@Node "Ogre" "Chaos.Guide/Ogre"
@Next "OgreAssassin"
@Prev "Nuke"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ogre
====

   The ogre is similar in ability to the gorilla, the troll, and the
goblin.

   Like these other creatures the ogre is very useful in a supporting
role in a major offensive but best avoid lone conflicts.


@EndNode

@Node "OgreAssassin" "Chaos.Guide/OgreAssassin"
@Next "OgreMage"
@Prev "Ogre"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ogre Assassin
=============

   The Ogre Assassin is a battle hardened ogre.  He has been specially
trained in a full gamut of lethal combat techniques and forms a
dependable attack creature where there is a need to get in quick and do
damage.


@EndNode

@Node "OgreMage" "Chaos.Guide/OgreMage"
@Next "OgreWarrior"
@Prev "OgreAssassin"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ogre Mage
=========

   Some ogres receive special training in the use of magic. These ogres
enjoy casting fireballs at opponents over a great distance. They are
also trained in the medical arts.

   They are identical to the standard ogre in appearance.


@EndNode

@Node "OgreWarrior" "Chaos.Guide/OgreWarrior"
@Next "Omnibiologist"
@Prev "OgreMage"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ogre Warrior
============

   The warrior ogre is a battle hardened ogre.  They fight with
considerably more vigour than the standard orge and can take more
punishment before they will succumb to exhaustion.

   They have little time for magic.


@EndNode

@Node "Omnibiologist" "Chaos.Guide/Omnibiologist"
@Next "OptometronofOmniscience"
@Prev "OgreWarrior"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Omnibiologist
=============

   The Omnibiologist is a Biologist, Exobiologist, Chronobiologist,
Xenobiologist and Exoplanar-Biologist all rolled into one.  He is a
complete master of both Botany and Zoology.  He can instantly recognize
any lifeform from any time-period, or from any other planet, or even
from any other plane of existence.  Upon viewing any scroll, he can
recite from memory the complete statistics for that creature.


@EndNode

@Node "OptometronofOmniscience" "Chaos.Guide/OptometronofOmniscience"
@Next "Oracle"
@Prev "Omnibiologist"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Optometron of Omniscience
=========================

   He who posesses the Optometron of Omniscience will know everything.
You will always know what is under any explored cell. You will always
know which spells are which during your bonus spell selections. You
will always know the stats of ANY scroll that you examnine. You will be
able to freely read the minds of the other wizards to know what spells
are in their spell-lists. + more! The Optometron of Omniscience is
functionally equivalent to possessing a Recognomancer and Burstroem's
Browser + more.

   During the spell-selection phase, just press CTRL-# to browse through
another player's spell-list. E. G. press ctrl-2 to peek at player 2's
spell-list.


@EndNode

@Node "Oracle" "Chaos.Guide/Oracle"
@Next "OrangeJelly"
@Prev "OptometronofOmniscience"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Oracle
======

   The Oracle has a Crystal Ball which benefits the controlling wizard.
A Crystal Ball removes the need for your wizard to have line of sight
in order to cast a spell.

   With the Crystal Ball, your wizard can "see" everywhere. Range
restrictions still apply as usual.


@EndNode

@Node "OrangeJelly" "Chaos.Guide/OrangeJelly"
@Next "Orc"
@Prev "Oracle"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Orange Jelly
============

   Yet another growth.  Orange jelly grows very quickly but is
correspondingly weak and even an orc has some chance of killing a piece
of jelly.

   Use an orange jelly when you want to quickly clog up an area of the
board.


@EndNode

@Node "Orc" "Chaos.Guide/Orc"
@Next "Orcs"
@Prev "OrangeJelly"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Orc
===

   The orc is typical of many exceedingly common species in having very
limited abilities.  Free orcs band together in tribes but those under a
wizard have deserted their tribes and pledged loyalty to their wizard.
Orcs are easily slain and are only of minimal use.  Their greatest
asset is their frequency.

   They hate elves and will kill them whenever possible but would
rather avoid the stronger ogre. Orcs are scavengers, though not
particularly efficient ones.


@EndNode

@Node "Orcs" "Chaos.Guide/Orcs"
@Next "ParadigmShift"
@Prev "Orc"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Orcs
====

   Sometimes when an orc is cast he will con a few friends into joining
your side.  Up to eight orcs in total may be obtained.  Although a
single orc offers little, a group of eight is very useful for blocking
generators or in the early stages of the game.


@EndNode

@Node "ParadigmShift" "Chaos.Guide/ParadigmShift"
@Next "ParalyzationBeam"
@Prev "Orcs"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Paradigm Shift
==============

   Wizards generally maintain their forces of undeads by continual
mental domination of the objects concerned.  This spell tweaks the
minds of all wizards so that all the undeads once again become only
potentials.  This means all undeads currently on the board will be
removed.

   However, it cannot cleanse them completely and all such undeads will
reappear on their controlling wizard's spell list. Indepedent undeads
will be utterly destroyed. Normally living creatures which have been
raised will also suffer the same fate. The undeads of the caster are
not immune because of the wide area pulse this spell creates.

   The spell is best used when you have few or no undeads of your own
and is particularly effective when there are many independent undeads.


@EndNode

@Node "ParalyzationBeam" "Chaos.Guide/ParalyzationBeam"
@Next "Passage"
@Prev "ParadigmShift"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Paralyzation Beam
=================

   Causes your wizard to emit a Beam of Paralyzation which will drain 7
points of movement from EVERYTHING in the chosen direction.  If the
target does not have at least 7 points of movement then the beam causes
6 life points of damage for every movement point less than 7.

   This beam does not affect scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "Passage" "Chaos.Guide/Passage"
@Next "Pegasus"
@Prev "ParalyzationBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Passage
=======

   A special ability for the wizard, which enables a wizard to pass
through any distance of occupied space and to emerge on the first
vacant piece of ground. The movement is instantaneous in the given
direction.

   If you are mounted or meditating then that object will accompany as
you pass.


@EndNode

@Node "Pegasus" "Chaos.Guide/Pegasus"
@Next "Pit"
@Prev "Passage"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Pegasus
=======

   The pegasus is a winged horse and may be ridden by the wizard.  The
pegasus can be used to carry the wizard to safety or to mount aerial
attacks on the enemy.

   If the pegasus is flown with a manticore or gryphon an effective
combat group can be formed.


@EndNode

@Node "Pit" "Chaos.Guide/Pit"
@Next "PlasmaBeam"
@Prev "Pegasus"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Pit
===

   A deep hole in the ground.  Any ground ridden creature attempting to
cross the pit will fall in and instantly die.  However, the creature
will fill in the pit and it will no longer be effective.

   Up to eight pits can be created at considerable distance, line of
sight is not required.


@EndNode

@Node "PlasmaBeam" "Chaos.Guide/PlasmaBeam"
@Next "PlatinumDragon"
@Prev "Pit"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Plasma Beam
===========

   Causes the wizard to emit a beam of plasma which will blast
everything in its passage as it streaks across the world in the chosen
direction.  Simply pick a cell adjacent to the wizard to specify the
direction.

   The wizard's own creatures are not immune to the beam.


@EndNode

@Node "PlatinumDragon" "Chaos.Guide/PlatinumDragon"
@Next "Points"
@Prev "PlasmaBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Platinum Dragon
===============

   The platinum dragon is the king of the good dragons.  A summons can
only be granted through meditation.  The platinum dragon has the
highest stamina of any creature, can attack as well as a vampire, fly,
and make use of a breath weapon.

   His breath is so strong that it is likely to start an elemental fire,
similar to that produced by the Fire spell. He has exceptional
intelligence and self-healing ability.


@EndNode

@Node "Points" "Chaos.Guide/Points"
@Next "PoisonDagger"
@Prev "PlatinumDragon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Points
======

   When competing for honour against other wizards it is desirable that
your final score reflects your ability.  This simple spell awards your
wizard 100 points in reflection of his greatness.  Unfortunately, the
spell does nothing to assist your fate in the world.

   The spell is best cast when you are stuck in a corner with no room
to cast a more productive spell. The spell is most beneficial in
limited turn games where you are playing solely for points.


@EndNode

@Node "PoisonDagger" "Chaos.Guide/PoisonDagger"
@Next "Pool"
@Prev "Points"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Poison Dagger
=============

   A spell which causes the chosen target to stop attacking life force
and turn to more sinister means of accomplishing the same task.  The
chosen target will instead infect during combat.  The infection is very
strong and will quickly mitigate the recovery rate of strong creatures
leading swiftly to death.

   For humanoid races this spell gives the combatant an infected
dagger, for other creatures appropriate action is taken, ranging from
poisonous fangs to astral viruses. The dagger does 5 points of damage.


@EndNode

@Node "Pool" "Chaos.Guide/Pool"
@Next "PowerWall"
@Prev "PoisonDagger"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Pool
====

   This little puddle is much more than it appears.  Creatures placed
next to the pool will heal their wounds much faster than normal.  The
healing will work on any nearby creature irrespective of the owner,
thus great care should be taken in the placing of the pool to ensure
your creatures derive the maximum benefit.


@EndNode

@Node "PowerWall" "Chaos.Guide/PowerWall"
@Next "Pox"
@Prev "Pool"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Power Wall
==========

   A powerful, nearly indestructable type of wall to block up your
enemies.  It is quite rare, and only one piece is granted, so use it
thoughtfully.


@EndNode

@Node "Pox" "Chaos.Guide/Pox"
@Next "PoxShield"
@Prev "PowerWall"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Pox
===

   The pox is a highly infectious and contagious disease which is
spread by proximity.  Creatures infected with the pox will slowly wilt
and may eventually die.  Wizards are not immune to its effects but can
be protected with a pox shield.

   All creatures can be cured of the pox by the cure spell. This spell
allows you to infect one creature with the disease.


@EndNode

@Node "PoxShield" "Chaos.Guide/PoxShield"
@Next "Protection"
@Prev "Pox"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Pox Shield
==========

   A special shield for the wizard to guard against the pox.


@EndNode

@Node "Protection" "Chaos.Guide/Protection"
@Next "Pseudodragon"
@Prev "PoxShield"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Protection
==========

   A magical shield specifically for the wizard.  This should be
applied after your wizard has been magically attacked to restore the
wizard's shield.

   Applying the shield to a wizard with maximum magical protection will
give additional long term protection.


@EndNode

@Node "Pseudodragon" "Chaos.Guide/Pseudodragon"
@Next "Pyrohydra"
@Prev "Protection"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Pseudodragon
============

   An imitation dragon which is considerably weaker than a real dragon,
but which will strike fear into opponents who have not witnessed one
before.


@EndNode

@Node "Pyrohydra" "Chaos.Guide/Pyrohydra"
@Next "Pyrotechnics"
@Prev "Pseudodragon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Pyrohydra
=========

   The pyrohydra is an extremely lethal variant of the standard hydra.
The pyrohydra is able to emit a burst of fire from all of its heads
simultaneously. The temperature and destructiveness of this breath
exceeds that of all but the strongest dragons. The range of the breath
is rather limited.

   A pyrohydra can only be obtained by meditation and even then is
rather unlikely. Most other living creatures should not risk
approaching a pyrohydra.


@EndNode

@Node "Pyrotechnics" "Chaos.Guide/Pyrotechnics"
@Next "Python"
@Prev "Pyrohydra"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Pyrotechnics
============

   Causes the wizard to emit a volley of rockets into several nearby
cells.  The spell is hard to control and often the wizards own
creations may suffer some impacts.

   The spell is best used when the wizard is surrounded by weak
opposition creatures. The rockets are particularly effective as they
often explode inside their targets.


@EndNode

@Node "Python" "Chaos.Guide/Python"
@Next "Quench"
@Prev "Pyrotechnics"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Python
======

   A snake which kills its prey by constriction.  The snake is,
however, not poisonous and therefore not feared by larger creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "Quench" "Chaos.Guide/Quench"
@Next "Quickshot"
@Prev "Python"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Quench
======

   This spell extinguishes all fires in the world, irrespective of the
owner.  It is only available by meditation.


@EndNode

@Node "Quickshot" "Chaos.Guide/Quickshot"
@Next "RaiseDead"
@Prev "Quench"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Quickshot
=========

   Advanced rapid-fire training for a wizard.  Allows the wizard to
shoot with a bow three times instead of once.


@EndNode

@Node "RaiseDead" "Chaos.Guide/RaiseDead"
@Next "RangeBoost"
@Prev "Quickshot"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Raise Dead
==========

   The Raise Dead spell is a highly sought after spell.  It enables a
wizard to bring a corpse back from the dead as an undead.  Whatever is
raised comes back from the dead as if it had just been cast by the
wizard except that it will be an undead.

   Don't be too quick to use your raise dead spell, but don't hold back
on it for too long either. The spell has only a short range and
requires line of sight.


@EndNode

@Node "RangeBoost" "Chaos.Guide/RangeBoost"
@Next "RangeDrainBeam"
@Prev "RaiseDead"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Range Boost
===========

   Range Boost improves the ranged combat abilities of any creature
which has a shooting weapon, including dragons, elves, wizards with
bows, pyrohydra and so on.  It has no effect on creatures without some
initial ability.

   Range Boost increases both the range and the damage of ranged combat
by +4.


@EndNode

@Node "RangeDrainBeam" "Chaos.Guide/RangeDrainBeam"
@Next "Recognomancer"
@Prev "RangeBoost"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Range Drain Beam
================

   Causes your wizard to emit a beam of Range Draining which will drain
4 points of range and 4 points of ranged combat from EVERYTHING in the
chosen direction.

   It will not reduce below 0.


@EndNode

@Node "Recognomancer" "Chaos.Guide/Recognomancer"
@Next "RecoverBoost"
@Prev "RangeDrainBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Recognomancer
=============

   The Recognomancer is similar to the Omnibiologist but he recognizes
everything.

   He also carries a deadly magic staff, making him much more lethal in
magic combat.


@EndNode

@Node "RecoverBoost" "Chaos.Guide/RecoverBoost"
@Next "RecoverDrainBeam"
@Prev "Recognomancer"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Recover Boost
=============

   This spell will increase its target's ability to heal wounds,
provided of course the recovery rate in not already at maximum.

   The spell is best cast on your wizard or a strong creature such as a
hydra or crocodile or on an undead.


@EndNode

@Node "RecoverDrainBeam" "Chaos.Guide/RecoverDrainBeam"
@Next "RedDragon"
@Prev "RecoverBoost"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Recover Drain Beam
==================

   Causes your wizard to emit a Beam of Poision which will drain 7
points from the life-recovery of EVERYTHING in the chosen direction
except scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "RedDragon" "Chaos.Guide/RedDragon"
@Next "Reflector"
@Prev "RecoverDrainBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Red Dragon
==========

   The red dragon is slightly superior to the green dragon in several
respects.  Like all dragons, a red dragon should not be attacked in an
ad hoc manner.

   If you wish to kill a red dragon you are going to need some real
muscle.  The red dragon has medium magical resistance.


@EndNode

@Node "Reflector" "Chaos.Guide/Reflector"
@Next "Reincarnate"
@Prev "RedDragon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Reflector
=========

   A special shield for a wizard which protects the wizard against
ranged combat.  Any incoming arrow, missile or dragon breath undergoes
a phase shift and is redirected to the source of the attack.

   The shield is not effective against normal combat or magical attacks.


@EndNode

@Node "Reincarnate" "Chaos.Guide/Reincarnate"
@Next "Replicate"
@Prev "Reflector"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Reincarnate
===========

   Gives a creature a reincarnation sequence.  Once killed a creature
possessing this important property will not disappear altogether but
will return to life as another, usually weaker, creature.

   The giant beetle is the final state for living creatures, and the
imp is the final state for undeads.


@EndNode

@Node "Replicate" "Chaos.Guide/Replicate"
@Next "Repulsion"
@Prev "Reincarnate"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Replicate
=========

   Replicate makes a clone of the chosen creature.  The clone will
belong to the same player as the original, so you best replicate one of
your own creatures.  The copy is identical in every respect.  Replicate
will fail if there is no empty space adjacent to the creature to be
duplicated.

   Replicating any Wizard causes prolonged disorientation and confusion
in the caster (and everyone else for that matter). Replicating a Wizard
can cause hallucinations, delusions, agitation and/or anger in certain
persons.


@EndNode

@Node "Repulsion" "Chaos.Guide/Repulsion"
@Next "Request"
@Prev "Replicate"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Repulsion
=========

   A spell which attempts to create space around a wizard.  Everything
near the wizard is forced to move out a cell.


@EndNode

@Node "Request" "Chaos.Guide/Request"
@Next "Restoration"
@Prev "Repulsion"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Request
=======

   Sometimes a wizard does not have time to formulate a summons for a
particular creature.  In this spell the wizard incants at speed and the
result is unpredictable.

   You may get any creature as a result.


@EndNode

@Node "Restoration" "Chaos.Guide/Restoration"
@Next "Resurrection"
@Prev "Request"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Restoration
===========

   Restoration restores a creature to its original mint condition.  It
also works on inanimate objects.


@EndNode

@Node "Resurrection" "Chaos.Guide/Resurrection"
@Next "Reveal"
@Prev "Restoration"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Resurrection
============

   Resurrection will resurrect any 1 creature from the realm of the
dead and bring it back to the land of the living under your control.


@EndNode

@Node "Reveal" "Chaos.Guide/Reveal"
@Next "Ride"
@Prev "Resurrection"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Reveal
======

   Reveal is the opposite of cloak.  Using reveal on a non-cloaked
creature does nothing, and is a waste of the spell.  Using reveal on a
cloaked creature will destroy the cloak rendering the creature visible
again.  Once revealed the creature can be attacked as per normal.

   Reveal works anywhere and does not require line of sight.


@EndNode

@Node "Ride" "Chaos.Guide/Ride"
@Next "Robot"
@Prev "Reveal"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ride
====

   Special training for the wizard which enables him to ride dragons as
well as the usual creatures.  In addition the wizard will be able to
mount elephants, dinosaurs, and the bird lord.


@EndNode

@Node "Robot" "Chaos.Guide/Robot"
@Next "Rock"
@Prev "Ride"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Robot
=====

   A very strong battle machine controlled by the wizard.  A robot can
only be destroyed by beating it to sheet metal.

   Robots are comparable to stone giants in abilities but much rarer
and more demanding on the casting wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "Rock" "Chaos.Guide/Rock"
@Next "Roper"
@Prev "Robot"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Rock
====

   3 large stones that function in a similar way to pieces of walls.
However, they can be cast on dead creatures unlike walls.


@EndNode

@Node "Roper" "Chaos.Guide/Roper"
@Next "Sanctuary"
@Prev "Rock"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Roper
=====

   Once cast, a roper moves and fights on its own accord but remains
loyal to the casting wizard.  The roper has six rope like limbs which
it uses to snare opponents and choke them to death.

   The roper is normally immobile but will occasionally teleport itself
to a new location.


@EndNode

@Node "Sanctuary" "Chaos.Guide/Sanctuary"
@Next "Scavengerism"
@Prev "Roper"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Sanctuary
=========

   Allows a wizard to recover quicker from any wounds received by
boosting his recovery rate to the maximum.


@EndNode

@Node "Scavengerism" "Chaos.Guide/Scavengerism"
@Next "Seismology"
@Prev "Sanctuary"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Scavengerism
============

   Scavengerism provides +8 Scavenging to any scavenger or +4
scavenging to any nonscavenger.  A scavenger eats corpses.  Bon
Appétit!


@EndNode

@Node "Seismology" "Chaos.Guide/Seismology"
@Next "Separation"
@Prev "Scavengerism"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Seismology
==========

   This spell will train all creatures on your team in the
seismological arts.  The training is so good that henceforth, any enemy
creature within 7 squares will automatically be detected.

   However this will not allow you to detect any creature which cannot
be detected by its earthly vibrations; thus, galloping horses can be
detected but inanimate objects, slithering snakes and floating ghosts
cannot.


@EndNode

@Node "Separation" "Chaos.Guide/Separation"
@Next "Shadow"
@Prev "Seismology"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Separation
==========

   This spell breaks any alliance your wizard is currently in.  It is
useful when weak wizards force you into unwanted alliances.


@EndNode

@Node "Shadow" "Chaos.Guide/Shadow"
@Next "ShadowCity"
@Prev "Separation"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Shadow
======

   This horrible undead creature is nearly invisible and drains an
enemie's strength merely by touch.  They are fast moving and quite
strong.  They have little magical resistance and the best way to
destroy a shadow is by a magic bolt or similar weapon.


@EndNode

@Node "ShadowCity" "Chaos.Guide/ShadowCity"
@Next "ShadowDragon"
@Prev "Shadow"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Shadow City
===========

   A mysterious safe haven for the wizard.  It is a home of the dead
and as such normal creatures should avoid coming in contact with a
shadow city.  It essentially behaves as an undead.  These havens are
much rarer than magic castles or dark citadels.

   When they collapse with a resident wizard the potential benefits are
high.  It is unlikely the city will be detroyed by attack.


@EndNode

@Node "ShadowDragon" "Chaos.Guide/ShadowDragon"
@Next "ShadowWood"
@Prev "ShadowCity"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Shadow Dragon
=============

   A partial reincarnation of a previously living dragon.  A dragon
which is due to be reincarnated is likely to become a shadow dragon.
The spell can also be cast directly, but is very rare.


@EndNode

@Node "ShadowWood" "Chaos.Guide/ShadowWood"
@Next "ShamblingMound"
@Prev "ShadowDragon"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Shadow Wood
===========

   The shadow wood is a useful tree when they are on your side.  The
shadow wood cannot move but it can attack any enemy creature that
strays into an adjacent square.

   Unlike the magic wood the shadow wood cannot be used for meditation
by a wizard. Each cast allows for 6 trees to be conjured up to 12 cells
away from the wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "ShamblingMound" "Chaos.Guide/ShamblingMound"
@Next "ShapeChanger"
@Prev "ShadowWood"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Shambling Mound
===============

   The Shambling Mound is some sort of weird ambulatory plant type of
thing.  It is also the most intelligent plant life known to man.

   It has superior scavenging and exophagy characteristics and is
completely omnivorous. As long as the Shambling Mound has a corpse to
sink its web of tangled roots into, it will be difficult to kill in
direct combat.


@EndNode

@Node "ShapeChanger" "Chaos.Guide/ShapeChanger"
@Next "Shocker"
@Prev "ShamblingMound"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Shape Changer
=============

   This special creature has no single form, but can appear as a lion,
a bear, or a crocodile.  The abilities of the shape changer slightly
exceed those of its constituent forms.

   The shape changer is only available by meditation.


@EndNode

@Node "Shocker" "Chaos.Guide/Shocker"
@Next "Simulacrum"
@Prev "ShapeChanger"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Shocker
=======

   Fits the recipent with an electromagnetic pulse generator which will
output one isotropic high energy pulse per round.  Essentially this
means enemy creatures adjacent to this creature will suffer an
additional wounding at the end of each round.

   The pulse is extremely deadly and given the choice an opponent would
be better off standing adjacent to 2 wasp nests simultaneously.


@EndNode

@Node "Simulacrum" "Chaos.Guide/Simulacrum"
@Next "SingularEarthbind"
@Prev "Shocker"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Simulacrum
==========

   A weaker form of the Replicate spell.  A copy of the chosen target
is made.  The copy will belong to the same player as the original.  The
copy, however, will be reasonably weak.

   Simulacrumming one's own wizard causes prolonged disorientation.


@EndNode

@Node "SingularEarthbind" "Chaos.Guide/SingularEarthbind"
@Next "Skeleton"
@Prev "Simulacrum"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Singular Earthbind
==================

   This spell does not require line of sight and works over the entire
world.  The target of this spell loses their wings and can no longer
fly.


@EndNode

@Node "Skeleton" "Chaos.Guide/Skeleton"
@Next "Sleep"
@Prev "SingularEarthbind"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Skeleton
========

   The skeleton is a magically animated human skeleton having no
intelligence or magical resistance and is the weakest undead.
Skeletons are easily conjured so they are a very common undead.

   The skeleton is useful for holding living creatures at bay but
quickly dies when attacked by any other type of undead.


@EndNode

@Node "Sleep" "Chaos.Guide/Sleep"
@Next "Slow"
@Prev "Skeleton"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Sleep
=====

   The sleep spell as the name suggests can be used to put a creature to
sleep.  Sleep does not work on wizards or on growths like gooey blobs.
Once asleep a creature cannot move or attack.  It is possible to attack
sleeping creatures.  The spell can be reversed by a wake spell.

   The pair sleep-wake presents an alternative to using a subversion
spell, but be aware that any wizard can use either spell. Sleep spells
are best reserved for use on strong opponents. The sleep state is
identical to that induced on creatures when a wizard dies.


@EndNode

@Node "Slow" "Chaos.Guide/Slow"
@Next "SluggishnessBeam"
@Prev "Sleep"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Slow
====

   The slow spell works over the entire world and does not require line
of sight.  The target will only be able to move a single cell at a
time.  Does not affect ranged combat.  Up to 3 creatures may be slowed
down.


@EndNode

@Node "SluggishnessBeam" "Chaos.Guide/SluggishnessBeam"
@Next "Solar"
@Prev "Slow"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Sluggishness Beam
=================

   Causes your wizard to emit a Beam of Sluggishness which will drain 7
points of maneuverability from EVERYTHING in the chosen direction.  If
the target does not have at least 7 points of maneuver then the beam
causes 6 life points of damage for every maneuver point less than 7.

   This beam does not affect scrolls.


@EndNode

@Node "Solar" "Chaos.Guide/Solar"
@Next "Spectator"
@Prev "SluggishnessBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Solar
=====

   A powerful undead spirit which would normally only serve a good
deity, but under exceptional circumstances will aid a wizard.  When
their assistance is given they will do so on their own accord.
However, the solar will remain loyal to its casting wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "Spectator" "Chaos.Guide/Spectator"
@Next "Spectre"
@Prev "Solar"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Spectator
=========

   An observant creature that has little interest in battle. However,
prolonged exposure to this creature can cause loss of maneuverability
rating.


@EndNode

@Node "Spectre" "Chaos.Guide/Spectre"
@Next "Speed"
@Prev "Spectator"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Spectre
=======

   The spectre is a powerful undead human having an existence in its own
right, unlike skeletons and zombies which are maintained continuously by
the wizard.

   The spectre has abilities comparable to a wraith.


@EndNode

@Node "Speed" "Chaos.Guide/Speed"
@Next "Spider"
@Prev "Spectre"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Speed
=====

   Speed works over the entire world and does not require line of
sight.  The target will be able to move an incredible 10 cells per
turn.  This does not affect ranged combat.  Up to 2 creatures may be
speeded up.


@EndNode

@Node "Spider" "Chaos.Guide/Spider"
@Next "Spriggan"
@Prev "Speed"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Spider
======

   A menacing hinderance to the opposition.  Although unlikely to be
fatal to any opposition the spider takes some effort to kill.


@EndNode

@Node "Spriggan" "Chaos.Guide/Spriggan"
@Next "StandardWall"
@Prev "Spider"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Spriggan
========

   An ugly, dour cousin of the gnome, generally dwelling in ruins.
They do not normally associate with wizards, and hate being in the
company of many humanoid races.

   If they become stressed they may suddenly decide to take a nap.


@EndNode

@Node "StandardWall" "Chaos.Guide/StandardWall"
@Next "Still"
@Prev "Spriggan"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Standard Wall
=============

   This is the most common type of wall in practice.  Like the weak
wall this wall is vulnerable to magic attacks, but has a stronger
constituency making it less vulnerable to combat attack.

   Four pieces can be cast per spell over a limited distance. Line of
sight is required.


@EndNode

@Node "Still" "Chaos.Guide/Still"
@Next "Stomp"
@Prev "StandardWall"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Still
=====

   Still heals the world from all the wounds created by earthquakes.
However, it does not prevent the possibility of future earthquakes.


@EndNode

@Node "Stomp" "Chaos.Guide/Stomp"
@Next "StoneGiant"
@Prev "Still"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Stomp
=====

   Stomp inflicts 16 points of damage to the unlucky victim.


@EndNode

@Node "StoneGiant" "Chaos.Guide/StoneGiant"
@Next "StoneGolem"
@Prev "Stomp"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Stone Giant
===========

   Capable of killing fauns, elves, horses and giant rats in a single
blow, the stone giant is a truly awesome creature.  Stone giants have
been known to kill lesser dragons and even once a pyrohydra.  What's
more the stone giant is a brilliant defender.  Once in battle, however,
the giant must fight to the death, but usually the giant will emerge as
the victor.


@EndNode

@Node "StoneGolem" "Chaos.Guide/StoneGolem"
@Next "StonetoFlesh"
@Prev "StoneGiant"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Stone Golem
===========

   As the name suggests these unintelligent creations are made of stone
and are therefore very strong and can take much punishment.  The
crushing blow of a stone golem's fist is enough to deter most
assailants.

   They are, however, quite susceptible to magic attack.


@EndNode

@Node "StonetoFlesh" "Chaos.Guide/StonetoFlesh"
@Next "Storm"
@Prev "StoneGolem"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Stone to Flesh
==============

   This spell does NOT turn stone to flesh!  It transforms ANY inanimate
object into a creature which can be moved around like any other
creature.

   The recipient inanimate object will become a creature able to move
at least 2 squares and attack with at least 2 points of combat.


@EndNode

@Node "Storm" "Chaos.Guide/Storm"
@Next "StrongWall"
@Prev "StonetoFlesh"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Storm
=====

   Storm causes the wizard to emit a random volley of lightning bolts.
Due to the number of bolts produced the wizard will not be able to
control where they land or which creatures are affected.

   This spell should be used cautiously. It is best applied when the
wizard is surrounded by enemy creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "StrongWall" "Chaos.Guide/StrongWall"
@Next "Subversion"
@Prev "Storm"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Strong Wall
===========

   This kind of wall is only available through meditation.  Strong wall
is superior to weak wall and standard wall as it has inbuilt magical
resistance, making it much harder to destroy.

   Only 3 pieces are granted per spell.


@EndNode

@Node "Subversion" "Chaos.Guide/Subversion"
@Next "Summons"
@Prev "StrongWall"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Subversion
==========

   Subversion is an attempt to convince an enemy creature that its
interests might be better served if it had allegiance to your wizard.
The spell might or might not succeed.  More intelligent creatures are
less likely to change sides than stupid creatures.  You will never be
able to convince another wizard to join your side or any creature such
a wizard might be riding.

   Subversion can be attempted on any creature (including sleeping
creatures).  The spell requires line of sight. If the spell fails
nothing happens to either party. If the spell succeeds the target of
the spell immediately swaps to your side and will no longer respond to
the commands of its previous leader.


@EndNode

@Node "Summons" "Chaos.Guide/Summons"
@Next "Swap"
@Prev "Subversion"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Summons
=======

   Surrounds the wizard with a random selection of creatures.  This
spell is very useful in the early stages of the game.


@EndNode

@Node "Swap" "Chaos.Guide/Swap"
@Next "SwordofSassenrath"
@Prev "Summons"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Swap
====

   Allows you to select another player with which to swap your
position.  All creatures you currently control will become those of the
target while you will gain control of all his creatures.

   However, your spells and your inanimate objects will not be swapped.


@EndNode

@Node "SwordofSassenrath" "Chaos.Guide/SwordofSassenrath"
@Next "T-Rex"
@Prev "Swap"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Sword of Sassenrath
===================

   This spell works over the entire world and does not require line of
sight.  The recipient of the Sword of Sassenrath will gain 5 points of
combat and will suddenly be able to attack undeads.

   Due to the fact that this mighty weapon was forged by the Arch-Mage
Sassenrath himself (one of the most intelligent wizards to have ever
lived), the recipient will also become considerably more intelligent.
Any friendly unit ending its turn adjacent to the holder of the Sword of
Sassenrath will also tend to become more intelligent.


@EndNode

@Node "T-Rex" "Chaos.Guide/T-Rex"
@Next "Teleport"
@Prev "SwordofSassenrath"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

T-Rex
=====

   The Tyrannosaurus Rex is the most terrible and fearsome of the
carnivorous dinosaurs.  Despite its size this animal is surprisingly
swift and is a good match for any dragon.  It can kill many creatures
with a single bite.  It is capable of killing a lion, pegasus, bear, or
bird lord within two turns.

   The Tyrannosaurus is a perpetually hungry hunter/scavenger and will
quickly devour any corpses it can find.  Tyrannosaurus is best attacked
with magic.


@EndNode

@Node "Teleport" "Chaos.Guide/Teleport"
@Next "Telescope"
@Prev "T-Rex"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Teleport
========

   When a strong creature is attacking your wizard or when your wizard
is jammed in a tight spot a teleport spell is useful to jump you safely
to a new location.

   Select the empty cell you wish to move to and activate the spell,
your wizard will magically translocate to the specified location.


@EndNode

@Node "Telescope" "Chaos.Guide/Telescope"
@Next "Tempest"
@Prev "Teleport"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Telescope
=========

   This spell works over the entire world and does not require line of
sight.

   The Telescope raises the Sight Range of the recipient by 4 squares
so that he can make accurate maps much faster.


@EndNode

@Node "Tempest" "Chaos.Guide/Tempest"
@Next "TheExorcist"
@Prev "Telescope"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Tempest
=======

   A tempest is an air elemental which moves at its own volition.
Inanimate objects are not affected by a tempest.  Any creature falling
into a tempest will be propelled to a new random location (which is
sometimes desirable, but usually best avoided).

   There is a small chance that the transported creature will not
survive the ordeal.


@EndNode

@Node "TheExorcist" "Chaos.Guide/TheExorcist"
@Next "Thundermare"
@Prev "Tempest"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

The Exorcist
============

   The exorcist is very useful for purging the world of enemy undead
creatures by attacking their magical resistance.

   He is useless against living creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "Thundermare" "Chaos.Guide/Thundermare"
@Next "Torment"
@Prev "TheExorcist"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Thundermare
===========

   A rare enchantment over the standard horse.  This creature is very
rarely available as a free spell, instead most often occurring when a
wizard riding a horse successfully kills another creature with the
horse.

   The thundermare has numerous advantages over the standard horse,
although its base strength is only slightly higher than the normal
horse. Its biggest asset is its advanced combat training. The
thundermare is capable of lashing out with all hooves simultaneously
and still land back on them afterwards. The thundermare represents an
ideal safe haven for the wizard.  It has extreme magic resistance and
will probably only be killed in direct combat, if at all.


@EndNode

@Node "Torment" "Chaos.Guide/Torment"
@Next "TouchofGod"
@Prev "Thundermare"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Torment
=======

   This spell allows your wizard to influence the strength of creature
casts made by all the other wizards.  When another wizard casts a
creature its life force will be only 4 points, making it easy to kill.

   If you are lucky the effect will hold for several creature casts of
each wizard, but more likely it will work once for each wizard. It has
no effect on independents or generated creatures.


@EndNode

@Node "TouchofGod" "Chaos.Guide/TouchofGod"
@Next "Tower"
@Prev "Torment"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Touch of God
============

   A very powerful spell which can turn the weakest of creatures into an
extremely intelligent and powerful being.

   The spell can also be cast on the wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "Tower" "Chaos.Guide/Tower"
@Next "ToxicityBeam"
@Prev "TouchofGod"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Tower
=====

   The mystical powers of the Magic Tower allow it to absorb the
essence of any creature who enters it.

   The Tower starts out very short but as it becomes more powerful it
grows in size.  Any creature entering a tower adds all of its primary
statistcs to the statistics of the Tower.  Once a creature enters a
tower it can never leave because its essence becomes one with the tower
in a permanent and unbreakable bond.

   Wizards cannot enter towers.


@EndNode

@Node "ToxicityBeam" "Chaos.Guide/ToxicityBeam"
@Next "TribalDance"
@Prev "Tower"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Toxicity Beam
=============

   Causes your wizard to emit a Beam of Toxicity which introduces vile
toxins into EVERYTHING in the chosen direction except scrolls.  Each
affected target will lose 1 point of recovery from ALL of its stats

   Thus, the toxins will kill almost anything within several turns.


@EndNode

@Node "TribalDance" "Chaos.Guide/TribalDance"
@Next "Triple"
@Prev "ToxicityBeam"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Tribal Dance
============

   The Tribal Dance is an exotic and exciting dance that will so excite
and energize your creatures that they will all become amazingly
maneuverable!

   They gain an extra movement point too!


@EndNode

@Node "Triple" "Chaos.Guide/Triple"
@Next "Troll"
@Prev "TribalDance"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Triple
======

   This is a highly sought after spell which gives the wizard the
ability to make three attempts with each subsequent spell, for a
limited time. It is most valuable near the start of the game when
building your forces.

   You cannot triple a spell which grants multiple attempts.


@EndNode

@Node "Troll" "Chaos.Guide/Troll"
@Next "Turmoil"
@Prev "Triple"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Troll
=====

   The troll has an uncanny ability for being able to heal its wounds
very quickly but is a rather stupid creature.  Trolls enjoy a good
fight, but are more suitable as accomplices to a stronger creature such
as a stone giant in a major offensive.


@EndNode

@Node "Turmoil" "Chaos.Guide/Turmoil"
@Next "Turns"
@Prev "Troll"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Turmoil
=======

   Turmoil affects every square in the world.  Every cell is randomly
transposed to a new location.

   The result is very unpredictable and may or may not improve your
situation.  Often useful when attacking a well fortified opponent. This
spell is only available through meditation and is very rare.


@EndNode

@Node "Turns" "Chaos.Guide/Turns"
@Next "Ubiquiscope"
@Prev "Turmoil"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Turns
=====

   Are you tired of expending a large amount of energy struggling in
what seems to be a never ending battle?  This spell could be the
answer.  If the number of turns remaining exceeds 10 then this spell
will give everyone a major hurry up by cutting the number of remaining
turns to just 10.

   However, the spell is bipolar and if the number of turns remaining
is less than 10 then an additional 10 turns will be granted.


@EndNode

@Node "Ubiquiscope" "Chaos.Guide/Ubiquiscope"
@Next "Uncertainty"
@Prev "Turns"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Ubiquiscope
===========

   The Ubiquiscope is equivalent to a Crystal Ball + a Magic Wand
combined.  A highly desirable spell which removes the need for your
wizard to have line of sight in order to cast a spell.

   With the Ubiquiscope, your wizard can "see" everywhere. Range
restrictions still apply as usual, though each Ubiquiscope will add +1
to your casting range.


@EndNode

@Node "Uncertainty" "Chaos.Guide/Uncertainty"
@Next "Unicorn"
@Prev "Ubiquiscope"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Uncertainty
===========

   This spell allows the wizard to harness the energy provided for
under the quantum uncertainty principle.

   For several turns after casting this spell it is likely that
creatures will just pop into existence on the side of the casting
wizard.


@EndNode

@Node "Unicorn" "Chaos.Guide/Unicorn"
@Next "Vampire"
@Prev "Uncertainty"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Unicorn
=======

   Unicorns can be ridden by a wizard but have little else to recommend
for them.  While a unicorn's horn can inflict a serious wound most
unicorns are not particularly skilled in combat.


@EndNode

@Node "Vampire" "Chaos.Guide/Vampire"
@Next "Vanish"
@Prev "Unicorn"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Vampire
=======

   The vampire is amongst the most feared of all creatures, second only
to the demon.  The vampire has exceptional intelligence, excellent
fighting ability and a good magical resistance as well as endurance.
Vampires are known to have killed golden dragons in five attacks.

   A vampire must constantly feed on living creatures or it will die.
Vampires do not feed on the dead.


@EndNode

@Node "Vanish" "Chaos.Guide/Vanish"
@Next "Vengeance"
@Prev "Vampire"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Vanish
======

   Vanish causes the chosen target to move to the astral plane.  The
object will instantly disappear and not return for some rounds.

   The spell can be applied to anything including generators and enemy
wizards or even yourself.


@EndNode

@Node "Vengeance" "Chaos.Guide/Vengeance"
@Next "VioletFungi"
@Prev "Vanish"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Vengeance
=========

   Vengeance is used to seek vengeance against an opponent.  Vegeance
can only be applied to creatures.

   The chosen target suffers 3 points of damage to its magic
resistance. Line of sight is not required.


@EndNode

@Node "VioletFungi" "Chaos.Guide/VioletFungi"
@Next "Virtue"
@Prev "Vengeance"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Violet Fungi
============

   Once cast a violet fungi no longer responds to commands from its
creator, although it will not harm him in any way.

   The violet fungi releases toxic spores which reduce the stamina of
nearby opponents. Occasionally, a fungi may sprout additional fungi.


@EndNode

@Node "Virtue" "Chaos.Guide/Virtue"
@Next "Vitality"
@Prev "VioletFungi"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Virtue
======

   A vaporous blast of multichromatic light resulting in the death of
many white species.  The caster's own creatures are not immune.

   The following species are immediately vaporized: air elementals,
arctic wolves, derros, floating eyes, falcons, fauns, gryphons,
pegasii, giant rats, skeletons, stone giants and white dragons.


@EndNode

@Node "Vitality" "Chaos.Guide/Vitality"
@Next "Vodka"
@Prev "Virtue"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Vitality
========

   A strong encouragement to your creations.  This spells gives them
peace of mind which means that their wounds will heal at a faster rate
than normal.

   Its effect is cumulative.


@EndNode

@Node "Vodka" "Chaos.Guide/Vodka"
@Next "Volcano"
@Prev "Vitality"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Vodka
=====

   This spell causes bottles of Vodka to appear nearby all the creatures
controlled by the same wizard as your target.  All the creatures will be
very happy about receiving this free gift and will merrily chug it all
down.

   The end result is that they will all be drunk for 2 turns cumulative
and their combat ability will be effectively cut in half.


@EndNode

@Node "Volcano" "Chaos.Guide/Volcano"
@Next "Vortex"
@Prev "Vodka"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Volcano
=======

   This spell unleashes powerful tectonic forces resulting in the
creation of a small volcano.  Any creature nearby will become more
agile.

   However, the volcano is inherently unstable and can explode without
warning.


@EndNode

@Node "Vortex" "Chaos.Guide/Vortex"
@Next "VoxAngelica"
@Prev "Volcano"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Vortex
======

   A roaming temporal anomaly that moves slowly around the board.
Creatures caught up in the vortex will become temporally distorted.

   They are typically propelled several rounds into the future.


@EndNode

@Node "VoxAngelica" "Chaos.Guide/VoxAngelica"
@Next "VoxCelestes"
@Prev "Vortex"
@Toc "SpellDescriptions"

Vox Angelica
============

   Vox Angelica is Latin for Angelic Voice.  The Angelic Voice heals
all of your creations.


@EndNode

